 |dead-url=no
 }}</ref>，在此使用的语言达到800种<ref>{{Cite web |title=Endangered Language Alliance |url=http://elalliance.org/ |accessdate=2013-09-07 |year=2012 |archive-date=2013-11-09 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131109073458/http://elalliance.org/ |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="800source2">{{Cite web |title=Linguistics- Say what? |url=http://www.economist.com/node/21528592 |accessdate=2013-10-24 |date=2011-09-10 |publisher=The Economist |archive-date=2013-10-15 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131015115929/http://www.economist.com/node/21528592 |dead-url=no }}</ref>，而在2005年，全市有36%的人口是非美国出生的。

纽约的历史可以追溯至1624年，[[荷兰共和国|荷兰]]殖民者在这时候在此地建立贸易站，名为[[新阿姆斯特丹|新阿姆斯特丹]]<ref name="u-s-history.com">{{cite web|url=http://www.u-s-history.com/pages/h2122.html|title=United States History - History of New York City, New York|accessdate=2012-09-09|archive-date=2012-09-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120908100919/http://www.u-s-history.com/pages/h2122.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。1664年，纽约及其周边地区为英国所占<ref name="u-s-history.com" /><ref>
and were renamed ''New York'' after King [[查理二世_(英格兰)|Charles II of England]] granted the lands to his brother, the [[詹姆斯二世_(英格蘭)|Duke of York]].</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nps.gov/nr/travel/kingston/colonization.htm|title=KINGSTON Discover 300 Years of New York History DUTCH COLONIES|publisher=National Park Service, U.S. Department of the Interior|accessdate=2011-05-10|archive-date=2008-11-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20081123001850/http://www.nps.gov/nr//travel/kingston/colonization.htm|dead-url=no}}</ref>。美國建國後，紐約在1785年—1790年為[[首都|首都]]<ref name=senate>{{cite web
 |url=http://www.senate.gov/reference/reference_item/Nine_Capitals_of_the_United_States.htm
 |title=The Nine Capitals of the United States
 |publisher=[[美国参议院|United States Senate]]
 |accessdate=2008-09-07
 |archive-date=2016-03-20
 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160320084755/http://www.senate.gov/reference/reference_item/Nine_Capitals_of_the_United_States.htm
 |dead-url=no
 }}</ref>，1790年，纽约取代[[费城|费城]]成为美国第一大城市<ref>{{cite web
