纽约的[[贫富差距|贫富差距]]状况也较为突出。2005年，最富有的人口普查区的家庭收入中值为188,697美元，而在最贫困的人口普查区则为9,320美元<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.fiscalpolicy.org/SamRoberts4Sep05.htm |title=In Manhattan, Poor Make 2 Cents for Each Dollar to the Rich |author=Roberts, Sam |date=2005-04-09 |work=The New York Times |accessdate=2007-03-27 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070403204124/http://www.fiscalpolicy.org/SamRoberts4Sep05.htm |archivedate=2007-04-03 |dead-url=yes}}</ref>，导致这一差距的原因是高收入人群薪酬的增加和中低收入人群薪酬增长的停滞。2013年第一季度，纽约县的平均周薪为2,448美元，在全美所有县中为最高<ref>{{Cite web |title=County Employment and Wages Summary |url=http://www.bls.gov/news.release/cewqtr.nr0.htm |accessdate=2013-11-08 |date=2013-09-26 |publisher=Bureau of Labor Statistics, U.S. Department of Labor |archive-date=2014-09-20 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140920120326/http://www.bls.gov/news.release/cewqtr.nr0.htm |dead-url=no }}</ref>。纽约还是世界上最多亿万富翁的聚集地，数目超过排名第二至第六的美国城市的总和<ref>{{Cite web |title=The 20 Cities Where The Most Billionaires Live |url=http://www.businessinsider.com/top-20-cities-where-billionaires-live-2013-5 |date=2013-05-07 |work=[[商业内幕|Business Insider]] |access-date=2014-01-27 |archive-date=2021-04-17 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210417164552/https://www.businessinsider.com/top-20-cities-where-billionaires-live-2013-5 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=Mumbai sixth among top 10 global cities on billionaire count |url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2013-05-10/mumbai/39167878_1_billionaires-millionaires-top-10-cities |work=[[印度时报|Times of India]] |publisher=2013-05-10 |access-date=2014-01-27 |archive-date=2013-11-13 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131113182925/http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2013-05-10/mumbai/39167878_1_billionaires-millionaires-top-10-cities |dead-url=yes }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=Which cities do the world's millionaires and billionaires live in? |url=http://www.theguardian.com/news/datablog/2013/may/08/cities-top-millionaires-billionaires |date=2013-05-08 |work=[[衛報|The Guardian]] |access-date=2014-01-27 |archive-date=2021-03-22 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210322045417/https://www.theguardian.com/news/datablog/2013/may/08/cities-top-millionaires-billionaires |dead-url=no }}</ref>，其中前市长[[迈克尔·布隆伯格|迈克尔·布隆伯格]]便是亿万富翁之一<ref>{{Cite web |title=The World's Billionaires - Michael Bloomberg |url=http://www.forbes.com/profile/michael-bloomberg/ |accessdate=2013-02-24 |publisher=Forbes.com |archive-date=2013-07-16 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130716185626/http://www.forbes.com/profile/michael-bloomberg/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

=== 建築 ===
{{Further|纽约市建筑|纽约市最高建筑列表}}
[[File:Bedstuybrownstone1.jpg|缩略图]]區19世纪的褐石排房]]
[[File:OneWorldTradeCenter.jpg|缩略图]][[世界貿易中心一號大樓|世界貿易中心一號大樓]]]]
纽约有许多来自不同年代不同风格的建筑。老建筑旧至布鲁克林区1656年的[[盐屋|盐屋式建筑]]——{{Link-en|怀科夫宅|Wyckoff House}}，新建筑新至位于曼哈顿下城[[911事件|原爆点]]兴建中的世界最贵办公楼<ref>{{Cite web |title=As One World Trade Center soars, so do its costs |url=http://bottomline.msnbc.msn.com/_news/2012/01/31/10279406-as-one-world-trade-center-soars-so-do-its-costs |accessdate=2012-02-01 |publisher=msnbc.com |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120201180547/http://bottomline.msnbc.msn.com/_news/2012/01/31/10279406-as-one-world-trade-center-soars-so-do-its-costs |archivedate=2012-02-01 |deadurl=yes}}</ref>——[[世界贸易中心一号大楼|世界贸易中心一号大楼]]。

曼哈顿的布满摩天大楼的[[天际线|天际线]]广为人知，在历史上，纽约是世界上许多世界级高楼的所在地。截至2011年，纽约有5,937幢[[高层建筑物|高层建筑物]]，其中550幢高度超过100米，在这两项指标上都仅次于[[香港|香港]]位列世界第二<ref>{{cite web  |url=http://www.emporis.com/application/?nav=skylineranking&lng=3  |title=Emporis Skyline Ranking  |publisher=Emporis Corporation  |accessdate=2011-10-23  |archive-date=2012-03-04  |archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/65u0fbmbK?url=http://www.emporis.com/statistics/skyline-ranking  |dead-url=no  }}</ref><ref>{{cite web
  |url=http://www.emporis.com/application/?nav=skyline_ranking
  |title=Emporis Skyline Ranking
  |publisher=Emporis Corporation
  |accessdate=2011-10-23
  |archive-date=2011-06-04
  |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110604164900/http://www.emporis.com/application/?nav=skyline_ranking
  |dead-url=yes
  }}</ref>，同时有超过50幢[[纽约市最高建筑列表|高度超过200米]]，其中包括1913年建成的[[哥德复兴式建筑|哥德复兴式建筑]][[伍尔沃斯大楼|伍尔沃斯大楼]]，其装饰雕刻十分醒目，从百英尺下即可目视。

{{link-en|1916年都市規劃方案|1916 Zoning Resolution}}規定高樓必須採用[[街影|後縮]]式設計，且塔樓面積須為該地块的一定百分比，如此可使陽光照射至街道<ref>{{Cite journal |title=The Metropolitan Dimension of Early Zoning: Revisiting the 1916 New York City Ordinance |author=Fischler, Raphael |journal=Journal of the American Planning Association |year=1998 |volume=64(2)}}</ref>。两幢纽约的[[装饰风艺术|装饰风]]建筑——[[克莱斯勒大厦|克莱斯勒大厦]]（1930年建成）和[[帝国大厦|帝国大厦]]（1931年建成）及其顶端和不锈钢材质的尖塔便是此规划方案的结果。这两幢建筑各有十分独特的装饰风格（例如克莱斯勒大厦61楼角落的鹰饰），也被认为是装饰风的最佳代表<ref>{{Cite web |title=Favorites! 100 Experts Pick Their top 10 New York Towers |url=http://www.skyscraper.org/EXHIBITIONS/FAVORITES/fav_exhibits.htm# |accessdate=2008-09-01 |date=2006-01-22 |publisher=The Skyscraper Museum |archive-date=2012-10-27 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121027144019/http://www.skyscraper.org/EXHIBITIONS/FAVORITES/fav_exhibits.htm |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

建築技術的發展讓紐約市裡的低矮歐式傳統建築逐漸變成垂直攀升的[[摩天大樓|摩天大樓]]，特別是在商業區裡，形成了紐約市特別的城市景觀。據2009年統計，紐約有5,794座高樓，居全美第一，世界第二，僅次[[香港|香港]]<ref>{{Cite web |title=High-rise Buildings of New York City |url=http://www.emporis.com/en/wm/ci/bu/sk?id=101028 |accessdate=2008-08-22 |publisher=Emporis.com |archive-date=2007-04-23 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070423105802/http://www.emporis.com/en/wm/ci/bu/sk/?id=101028 |dead-url=no }}</ref>，其中有35座高度超過200米，是拥有最多摩天大楼的城市<ref name="Highrises">{{Cite web |title=Emporis Skyline Ranking |url=http://www.emporis.com/en/bu/sk/st/sr |accessdate=2008-06-16 |publisher=Emporis.com |archive-date=2008-05-15 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080515211251/http://www.emporis.com/en/bu/sk/st/sr/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>。目前纽约第一高楼[[帝国大厦|帝国大厦]]（楼板高381米，加天线447米）在1931—1972的41年里都是世界第一高楼，是世界上保持世界第一高楼最久的建筑。现在也是纽约主要的标志之一。{{Link-en|国际式|International Style (architecture)}}建筑的突出代表[[西格拉姆大厦|西格拉姆大厦]]（1957年建成）从正面可见其鲜明的古铜色[[工字梁|工字梁]]建筑结构，而[[康德納斯特大樓|康德納斯特大樓]]（2000年建成）则是美国摩天大楼中采用[[永续设计|绿色设计]]的代表<ref name="greenbuilding" />。

纽约住宅区的建筑特色多为雅致的褐石[[排屋|排屋]]、联排别墅和老旧的公寓楼，这些建筑约在1870年至1930年间大批建造<ref>{{Cite book |title=History of Housing in New York City: Dwelling Type and Change in the American Metropolis |last=Plunz, Richard A. |publisher=Columbia University Press |year=1990 |isbn=0-231-06297-4 |chapter=Chapters 3 [Rich and Poor] & 4 [Beyond the Tenement]}}</ref>。相比较之下，纽约还有其他人口不那么密集的区域，在这些区域内有较多独立式的建筑，风格多样，如{{Link-en|都铎复兴式建筑|Tudor Revival architecture|都铎复兴式}}和[[维多利亚式建筑|维多利亚式]]<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.nytimes.com/1998/03/01/realestate/if-you-re-thinking-living-riverdale-bronx-community-jealous-its-open-space.html?pagewanted=all&src=pm |title=If You're Thinking of Living In/Riverdale, the Bronx; A Community Jealous of Its Open Space |date=1998-03-01 |work=The New York Times |accessdate=2012-02-10 |archive-date=2021-04-17 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210417164641/https://www.nytimes.com/1998/03/01/realestate/if-you-re-thinking-living-riverdale-bronx-community-jealous-its-open-space.html?pagewanted=all&src=pm |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=New York Metro: 6 Affordable Neighborhoods |url=http://nymag.com/realestate/articles/affordable/ditmaspark.htm |accessdate=2012-02-10 |date=2001-09-17 |publisher=Nymag.com |archive-date=2018-06-30 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180630214349/http://nymag.com/realestate/articles/affordable/ditmaspark.htm |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.nytimes.com/2004/02/08/realestate/if-you-re-thinking-living-douglaston-queens-timeless-city-area-with-country-feel.html?pagewanted=all&src=pm |title=If You're Thinking of Living In/Douglaston, Queens; Timeless City Area, With a Country Feel |date=2004-02-08 |work=The New York Times |accessdate=2012-02-10 |archive-date=2021-04-17 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210417164652/https://www.nytimes.com/2004/02/08/realestate/if-you-re-thinking-living-douglaston-queens-timeless-city-area-with-country-feel.html?pagewanted=all&src=pm |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

在{{Link-en|纽约大火灾|Great Fire of New York|1835年纽约大火灾}}后，木制建筑兴建减少，石头和砖头成为了建筑的主要材质<ref name="lankevich-p82">Lankevich (1998), pp. 82–83; {{Cite book |title=New York: Old & New: Its Story, Streets, and Landmarks |last=Wilson, Rufus Rockwell |publisher=J.B. Lippincott |year=1902 |page=354}}</ref>。紐約与[[巴黎|巴黎]]的建築材質不同，巴黎用的是當地產的[[石灰石|石灰石]]，紐約則使用遠方採石場運來的石頭，有不同的質地和顏色，因此市容較多變化<ref>{{Cite book |title=The Landmarks of New York |url=https://archive.org/details/landmarksofnewyo0000diam_k8i2 |last=B. Diamonstein–Spielvoegel, Barbaralee |publisher=Monacelli Press |year=2005 |isbn=1580931545}} See also {{cite book |author=Whyte, William H. |title=The WPA Guide to New York City |year=1939 |publisher=New Press |isbn=1565843215}}</ref>。木质顶的[[水塔|水塔]]是纽约一种独特的建筑形式——在19世纪初，纽约市要求超过六层的建筑自建水塔，以防止底层的高水压导致城市水管破裂<ref>{{Cite web |title=Wondering About Water Towers |url=http://www.npr.org/templates/story/story.php?storyId=6567297 |accessdate=2008-09-01 |author=Elliot, Debbie |date=2006-12-02 |publisher=National Public Radio |archive-date=2008-11-19 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20081119120140/http://www.npr.org/templates/story/story.php?storyId=6567297 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。20世纪20年代，[[田园城市理论|田园城市理论]]开始在偏僻地带流行<ref>{{Cite book |title=722 Miles: The Building of the Subways and How They Transformed New York |last=Hood, Clifton |publisher=Johns Hopkins University Press |year=2004 |isbn=0-8018-5244-7 |pages=175–177}}</ref>。

=== 公園 ===
{{main|紐約市公園列表}}
纽约市的公园受到三套不同的公园体系管辖，包括[[美国国家公园管理局|美国国家公园管理局]]、纽约州公园管理局以及纽约市公园管理局。
根据2013年《{{link-en|公共土地公信力|The Trust for Public Land}}》公园排名榜报告，纽约市公园系统在美国人口最多的50大城市中位列第二，紧随明尼阿波利斯公园系统其后<ref>{{Cite web |title=New York Parks Rank No. 2 in a Survey of 50 U.S. cities |url=http://www.nytimes.com/2013/06/05/nyregion/new-york-citys-park-system-ranked-no-2-in-survey-of-50-cities.html?_r=0 |accessdate=2014-04-30 |archive-date=2021-04-17 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210417164713/https://www.nytimes.com/2013/06/05/nyregion/new-york-citys-park-system-ranked-no-2-in-survey-of-50-cities.html?_r=0 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。该排行榜基于分析公园大小、土地面积占全市面积百分比、在公园半英里内的城市居民百分比、每位居民花在公园服务的时间、每万名居民对应的运动场数量等各项数据的均值得出。
{{main|美国国家公园管理局}}
[[File:Liberty-statue-from-front.jpg|缩略图]]]]
{{Link-en|盖特韦国家休闲区|Gateway National Recreation Area}}占地达到{{convert|26000|acre|sqkm}}，其中大部分都位于纽约市<ref>{{Cite web |title=Discover the truly wild side of New York's metropolitan area |url=http://www.nps.gov/gate/index.htm |accessdate=2012-06-11 |publisher=nps.gov |archive-date=2021-04-17 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210417193939/https://www.nps.gov/gate/index.htm |dead-url=no }}</ref>。在其范围内包括位于布鲁克林和皇后区的{{Link-en|牙買加灣野生動物保護區|Jamaica Bay Wildlife Refuge}}，它是[[國家公園系統|國家公園系統]]中唯一的野生動物區，有面積達{{convert|9000|acre|sqkm}}的[[盐碱滩|盐碱滩]]、岛屿和水域，涵蓋[[牙買加灣|牙買加灣]]大部。

[[自由女神像国家纪念区|自由女神像国家纪念区]]和[[埃利斯岛|埃利斯岛移民博物馆]]都归美国国家公园管理局管辖，都同时属于纽约和新泽西两州。在纽约港同时还有{{Link-en|總督島國家紀念園區|Governors Island National Monument}}。在曼哈顿岛上有[[克林顿堡|克林顿堡国家纪念区]]、[[联邦国家纪念堂|联邦国家纪念堂]]、
{{Link-en|西奥多·罗斯福出生地|Theodore Roosevelt Birthplace National Historic Site}}、[[格兰特将军国家纪念堂|格兰特将军国家纪念堂]]、{{Link-en|非裔人埋葬地国家纪念区|African Burial Ground National Monument}}及{{Link-en|汉密尔顿住宅国家纪念区|Hamilton Grange National Memorial}}等。此外还有数百幢私人建筑被列入[[国家史迹名录|国家史迹名录]]或列为[[美国国家历史名胜|美国国家历史名胜]]，例如[[LGBT权利运动|同性恋权利运动]]的首发地，[[格林尼治村|格林尼治村]]的[[石墙酒吧|石墙酒吧]]<ref>{{Cite web |title=Workforce Diversity The Stonewall Inn, National Historic Landmark National Register Number: 99000562 |url=http://www.nps.gov/diversity/stonewall.htm |accessdate=2011-04-30 |publisher=National Park Service, U.S. Department of the Interior |archive-date=2016-03-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160306222059/http://www.nps.gov/diversity/stonewall.htm |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=Obama inaugural speech references Stonewall gay-rights riots |url=http://www.northjersey.com/news/2012_Presidential_Election/Obama_inaugural_speech_references_Stonewall_riots.html |accessdate=2013-01-21 |date=2013-01-21 |publisher=North Jersey Media Group Inc |archive-date=2013-10-19 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131019080324/http://www.northjersey.com/news/2012_Presidential_Election/Obama_inaugural_speech_references_Stonewall_riots.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

==== 纽约州立公园 ====
纽约市内有7个州立公园<ref>{{Cite web |title=New York State Office of Parks, Recreation and Historic Preservation, New York City Region |url=http://www.nysparks.state.ny.us/parks/93/details.aspx |accessdate=2010-10-28 |publisher=Nysparks.state.ny.us |dead-url=yes |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110215035615/http://www.nysparks.state.ny.us/parks/93/details.aspx |archive-date=2011-02-15}}</ref>，其中包括自然保护区{{Link-en|粘土坑池塘州立公园|Clay Pit Ponds State Park Preserve}}和面积达{{convert|28|acre|m2}}，距哈德逊河河面{{convert|69|ft|m}}的{{Link-en|河岸州立公园|Riverbank State Park}}。

==== 纽约市立公园 ====
[[File:Bronx_Zoo_reindeer.jpg|缩略图]]是世界上最大的城市动物园<ref name="BronxZoo">{{Cite web |title=Bronx Zoo Animals & Exhibits |url=http://www.bronxzoo.com/animals-and-exhibits.aspx |accessdate=2013-06-02 |publisher=Wildlife Conservation Society |archive-date=2015-01-14 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150114073313/http://bronxzoo.com/animals-and-exhibits.aspx |dead-url=no }}</ref>。图为动物园中的[[驯鹿|驯鹿]]]]
紐約市有超過{{convert|28000|acre|sqkm}}的市立公園和超過{{convert|14|mi|km}}的公共海灘<ref>{{Cite web |title=Mayor Giuliani Announces Amount of Parkland in New York City has Passed 28,000-acre Mark |url=http://www.nyc.gov/html/om/html/99a/pr042-99.html |accessdate=2008-09-01 |date=1999-02-03 |publisher=New York City Mayor's Office |archive-date=2008-10-04 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20081004141450/http://www.nyc.gov/html/om/html/99a/pr042-99.html |dead-url=no }}; {{cite web |url=http://www.nycgovparks.org/facilities/beaches |title=Beaches |publisher=New York City Department of Parks & Recreation |accessdate=2008-09-01 |archive-date=2008-09-21 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080921020357/http://www.nycgovparks.org/facilities/beaches |dead-url=no }}</ref>。公园包括[[中央公園_(紐約市)|中央公園]]、[[展望公园_(布鲁克林)|展望公园]]、[[法拉盛草原可乐娜公园|法拉盛草原可乐娜公园]]、{{Link-en|森林公园 (皇后区)|Forest Park (Queens)|森林公园}}和[[华盛顿广场公园|华盛顿广场公园]]。{{Link-en|培罕湾公园|Pelham Bay Park}}是市内最大的公园，面积达到{{convert|2700|acres|sqkm}}<ref>{{Cite web |title=Pelham Bay Park Virtual Tour |url=http://www.nycgovparks.org/park-features/pelham-bay-park/virtual-tour |accessdate=2012-06-08 |publisher=NYC gov |dead-url=yes |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120616164717/http://www.nycgovparks.org/park-features/pelham-bay-park/virtual-tour |archive-date=2012-06-16}}</ref>。

*[[中央公園_(紐約市)|中央公園]]位于曼哈顿，面积{{convert|883|acre|km2}}，是全美造访人数最多的公园，每年游客达到2500万<ref name="TPL.org-CFCPE">{{Cite web |title=City Park Facts |url=http://www.tpl.org/tier3_cd.cfm?content_item_id=20531&folder_id=3208 |accessdate=2008-09-01 |date=June 2006 |publisher=The Trust for Public Land, Center for City Park Excellence |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070221010058/http://www.tpl.org/tier3_cd.cfm?content_item_id=20531&folder_id=3208 |archivedate=2007-02-21 |deadurl=yes}}</ref>。公园中有诸多景观，包括湖泊和池塘、滑冰场、[[中央公园动物园|中央公园动物园]]、{{Link-en|中央公园温室花园|Central Park Conservatory Garden}}、面积达{{convert|106|acre|km2}}的杰基·奥纳西斯水库。室内景观有[[美景城堡|美景城堡]]。
*[[展望公园_(布鲁克林)|展望公园]]位于布鲁克林，拥有面积达{{convert|90|acre|km2}}的草原、湖泊和林地<ref>{{Cite web |title=General Information |url=http://www.prospectpark.org/visit |accessdate=2008-09-01 |publisher=Prospect Park Alliance |archive-date=2008-09-13 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080913191648/http://www.prospectpark.org/visit |dead-url=no }}</ref>。
*[[法拉盛草原可乐娜公园|法拉盛草原可乐娜公园]]位于皇后区，是纽约第三大的公园，也是[[1939年世界博览会|1939年]]和[[1964年世界博覽會|1964年世界博覽會]]的举办地。
*布朗克斯區其中五分之一的面積（近{{convert|7000|acre|sqkm}}）屬於公共場地和公園，包含{{link-en|范可蘭公園|Van Cortlandt Park}}、{{Link-en|培罕湾公园|Pelham Bay Park}}、[[布朗克斯动物园|布朗克斯动物园]]和[[紐約植物園|紐約植物園]]<ref>[http://news.yahoo.com/s/ap_travel/20080630/ap_tr_ge/travel_trip_wild_green_bronx Ladies and gentlemen, the Bronx is blooming!] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110501203753/http://news.yahoo.com/s/ap_travel/20080630/ap_tr_ge/travel_trip_wild_green_bronx |date=2011-05-01 }} by Beth J. Harpaz, Travel Editor of [[美联社|The Associated Press]] (AP), June 30, 2008, retrieved on July 11, 2008</ref>。

