纽约市面積廣大，分為五個[[行政區_(紐約市)|行政區]]<ref>{{Cite book |title=Regionalism and realism: A Study of Government in the New York Metropolitan Area |last=Benjamin, Gerald, Richard P. Nathan |publisher=[[布鲁金斯学会|Brookings Institute]] |year=1990 |page=59}}</ref>，與[[紐約州|紐約州]]下轄的[[郡|郡]]重疊。每一行政區還可細分為街區，許多的街區有不同的歷史和特色。如果將這些行政區劃分為獨立的城市，其中四個街區（布魯克林、皇后區、曼哈頓島和布朗克斯）將會是全美前十多人居住的城市。

* '''[[曼哈頓|曼哈頓]]'''（纽约县）：人口最稠密的行政區<ref name="#1"/>，[[中央公園_(紐約市)|中央公園]]和纽约大部分[[摩天大樓|摩天大樓]]的所在地，大部分都位于哈德逊河口的曼哈顿岛上。曼哈顿也是紐約甚至世界的[[金融中心|金融中心]]，許多大企業的總部、[[聯合國|聯合國]]總部、许多重要的大学和文化景點都位于此处，其中还包含[[大都会博物馆|大都会博物馆]]等多座知名博物館、[[百老匯|百老匯]]區、[[格林威治村|格林威治村]]和[[麥迪遜廣場花園|麥迪遜廣場花園]]。曼哈頓可粗略區分為[[曼哈頓下城|下城]]、[[曼哈頓中城|中城]]和[[曼哈頓上城|上城]]，上城以中央公園為界可分為[[上西城|上西城]]和[[上東城|上東城]]，公園以北就是[[哈林區|哈林區]]。纽约的其他四个区被统称为“外区”。

* '''[[布朗克斯|布朗克斯]]'''（布朗克斯县）：最北的行政區，[[纽约洋基|纽约洋基]]的主场[[洋基体育场|洋基体育场]]位于此地。除了曼哈頓的[[大理石丘|大理石丘]]外，布朗克斯是紐約市唯一與[[美國本土|美國本土]]相接的區域。世界上最大的市内动物园<ref name=BronxZoo/>[[布朗克斯动物园|布朗克斯动物园]]也位于此地，面积达{{convert|265|acre|km2}}，居住动物达6,000头<ref>{{Cite book |title=New York City Museum Guide |url=https://archive.org/details/newyorkcitymuseu0000unse |last=Ward, Candace |publisher=Dover Publications |year=2000 |isbn=0-486-41000-5 |page=[https://archive.org/details/newyorkcitymuseu0000unse/page/n72 72]}}</ref>。同时，布朗克斯还是[[饶舌|饶舌乐]]和[[嘻哈|嘻哈文化]]的发源地<ref name="Toop-RapAttack2" />。

* '''[[布魯克林|布魯克林]]'''（国王县）：人口最多的行政區，位于长岛西端，在1898年以前仍是獨立的城市。此區的文化、社會和種族极富多元性，帶有独立藝術情調以及建築傳統。除了曼哈頓外，布魯克林是唯一有中心商業區的行政區。此外，此區還有一条長海岸線，其中的[[科尼島|科尼島]]于19世纪70年代设立，是全国最早的游乐设施之一<ref>{{Cite book |title=Coney Island: The People's Playground |last=Immerso, Michael |publisher=Rutgers University Press |year=2002 |isbn=0813531381 |page=3}}</ref>。

* '''[[皇后區|皇后區]]'''（皇后县）：面積最大的行政區，位于长岛布鲁克林的东侧，也是全美種族最多元的郡<ref name="queensdiverse">{{Cite news |url=http://www.nytimes.com/2006/07/04/nyregion/04fourth.html |title=In Queens, It's the Glorious 4th, and 6th, and 16th, and 25th... |author=O'Donnell, Michelle |date=2006-07-04 |publisher=New York Times |accessdate=2008-09-01 |archive-date=2009-04-15 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090415232104/http://www.nytimes.com/2006/07/04/nyregion/04fourth.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>，其人口成長的速度將會使該區打破布魯克林成為人口最多的行政區。过去此区由一些荷兰移民所创立的小城镇和村庄组成，今日则发展为重要的商业和住宅区。這裡也是全美唯一一個[[非裔美國人|非裔美國人]]收入大於白人的县（年收入約$52,000）<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.nytimes.com/2006/10/01/nyregion/01census.html?ref=nyregion |title=Black Incomes Surpass Whites in Queens |author=Roberts, Sam |date=2006-01-10 |publisher=The New York Times |accessdate=2008-09-01 |archive-date=2009-04-15 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090415232111/http://www.nytimes.com/2006/10/01/nyregion/01census.html?ref=nyregion |dead-url=no }}</ref>。皇后區有[[紐約大都會|紐約大都會]]的[[花旗球場|花旗球場]]，是[[美國網球公開賽|美國網球公開賽]]的舉辦地。交通方面，[[紐約都會區|紐約都會區]]的三个主要机场中有两个——[[甘迺迪國際機場|甘迺迪國際機場]]和[[拉瓜地亞機場|拉瓜地亞機場]]——位于此区（第三个是位于新泽西州[[纽瓦克_(新泽西州)|纽瓦克]]的[[纽瓦克自由国际机场|纽瓦克自由国际机场]]）。

* '''[[史泰登島|史泰登島]]'''（里士满县）：最郊區的行政區，分別藉由[[韋拉札諾海峽大橋|韋拉札諾海峽大橋]]和[[史泰登島渡輪|史泰登島渡輪]]與布魯克林和曼哈頓連接。史泰登島渡輪是紐約的相當熱門的景點，因為它能提供欣賞[[自由女神像|自由女神像]]、[[埃利斯島|埃利斯島]]和曼哈頓下城的最佳視野。在史泰登島中部有{{convert|2500|acres|km2}}的林带，其中有近{{convert|28|mi|km}}的步道和紐約市內最後一片無人破壞的森林<ref>{{Cite web |title=Staten Island Greenbelt | New York-New Jersey Trail Conference |url=http://www.nynjtc.org/park/staten-island-greenbelt |accessdate=2010-10-28 |publisher=Nynjtc.org |archive-date=2021-04-29 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210429230830/https://www.nynjtc.org/park/staten-island-greenbelt |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

== 文化与生活 ==
{{Further|纽约市文化}}
[[File:Metropolitan_Museum_of_Art_(The_Met)_-_Central_Park,_NYC.jpg|缩略图]]位于曼哈顿[[上东城|上东城]]{{Link-en|卡耐基山|Carnegie Hill}}的博物馆区，是世界上最大的博物馆<ref>{{Cite web |title=The Metropolitan Museum of Art General Information |url=http://www.metmuseum.org/en/about-the-museum/press-room/general-information?pg=1&rpp=50 |accessdate=2012-09-10 |publisher=The Metropolitan Museum of Art |archive-date=2012-04-18 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120418232003/http://metmuseum.org/en/about-the-museum/press-room/general-information?rpp=50&pg=1 |dead-url=no }}</ref>]]

[[冰岛|冰岛]]<ref name=culture1/>和[[拉脱维亚|拉脱维亚]]<ref name="culture2">{{Cite web |title=Consulate of Latvia in New York |url=http://www.latvia-newyork.org/english/ |accessdate=2013-02-17 |publisher=Consulate of Latvia |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130208223706/http://www.latvia-newyork.org/english/ |archivedate=2013-02-08 |deadurl=yes}}</ref>的[[领事|领事]]及[[纽约市立大学柏鲁克分校|纽约市立大学柏鲁克分校]]<ref name="culture3">{{Cite web |title=Introduction to Chapter 14: New York City (NYC) Culture |url=http://www.baruch.cuny.edu/nycdata/Culture/intro.htm |accessdate=2013-02-17 |publisher=The Weissman Center for International Business Baruch College/CUNY 2011 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130505181316/http://www.baruch.cuny.edu/nycdata/culture/intro.htm |archivedate=2013-05-05 |deadurl=yes}}</ref>都将纽约称作世界的文化首都，同样[[澳洲国家图书馆|澳洲国家图书馆]]在其收藏的一系列文章中也做了类似表述<ref name="culture1" />。作家[[汤姆·沃尔夫|汤姆·沃尔夫]]曾说：“文化似乎就在空气之中，就如天气一般<ref>{{Cite press release |title=Speeches: Tom Christopher Exhibit Opening |publisher=Consulate General of the United States: Frankfurt, Germany |date=2007-05-09 |url=http://frankfurt.usconsulate.gov/frankfurt/speech05092007b.html |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070723115555/http://frankfurt.usconsulate.gov/frankfurt/speech05092007.html |archivedate=2007-07-23 |accessdate=2008-09-01 |deadurl=yes}}</ref>。”

许多重要的美国的文化运动都在纽约展开，例如[[哈莱姆文艺复兴|哈莱姆文艺复兴]]便奠定了非裔美国人的文学经典<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.nytimes.com/1987/02/08/magazine/harlem-in-the-jazz-age.html?src=pm |title=HARLEM IN THE JAZZ AGE |date=1987-02-08 |newspaper=New York Times |accessdate=2012-05-31 |archive-date=2013-05-04 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130504150951/http://www.nytimes.com/1987/02/08/magazine/harlem-in-the-jazz-age.html?src=pm |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.nytimes.com/1998/05/24/arts/art-a-1920-s-flowering-that-didn-t-disappear.html?src=pm |title=ART; A 1920's Flowering That Didn't Disappear |date=1998-05-24 |newspaper=NY Times |accessdate=2012-05-31 |archive-date=2013-05-05 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130505034910/http://www.nytimes.com/1998/05/24/arts/art-a-1920-s-flowering-that-didn-t-disappear.html?src=pm |dead-url=no }}</ref>。在20世纪40年代，纽约是[[爵士乐|爵士乐]]的中心之一<ref name="Jazzzz">{{Cite web |title=Harlem Renaissance Music in the 1920s |url=http://www.1920s-fashion-and-music.com/Harlem-Renaissance-music.html |accessdate=2012-06-01 |publisher=1920s-fashion-and-music.com |archive-date=2012-10-13 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121013161750/http://www.1920s-fashion-and-music.com/Harlem-Renaissance-music.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>；在50年代是[[抽象表现主义|抽象表现主义]]艺术的中心；在70年代是[[嘻哈|嘻哈文化]]的发源地<ref name="BPOHPINY">{{Cite news |url=http://www.nytimes.com/2007/05/21/nyregion/21citywide.html?pagewanted=all |title=Will Gentrification Spoil the Birthplace of Hip-Hop? - New York |date=2007-05-21 |newspaper=NY Times |accessdate=2012-06-01 |archive-date=2021-04-17 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210417164840/https://www.nytimes.com/2007/05/21/nyregion/21citywide.html?pagewanted=all |dead-url=no }}</ref>；在七八十年代，纽约的[[朋克文化|朋克]]<ref>Harrington, Joe S. ''Sonic Cool: The Life & Death of Rock 'N' Roll''. pp. 324–30. 2002. Hal-Leonard. USA.</ref>和[[硬核朋克|硬核文化]]<ref>{{Cite web |title=SURVIVAL OF THE STREETS |url=http://www.vice.com/read/survival-of-the-streets-137-v16n9 |accessdate=2012-06-01 |publisher=Vice |archive-date=2016-10-23 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161023050118/http://www.vice.com/read/survival-of-the-streets-137-v16n9 |dead-url=no }}</ref>影响巨大。同时，犹太美国人文学在纽约也长期兴旺。

分领域来看，纽约对于文化的贡献在文学和视觉艺术方面有哈莱姆文艺复兴；在绘画方面有抽象表现主义（又称“纽约派”）；在音乐方面有[[嘻哈音乐|嘻哈音乐]]<ref name="Toop-RapAttack2">{{Cite book |title=Rap Attack 2: African Rap to Global Hip Hop |last=Toop |first=David |publisher=Serpents Tail |year=1992 |isbn=1-85242-243-2}}</ref>、[[朋克摇滚|朋克摇滚]]、[[骚沙音乐|骚沙音乐]]、[[迪斯科|迪斯科]]、{{Link-en|自由风音乐|Freestyle music}}、[[叮砰巷|叮砰巷]]及[[爵士乐|爵士乐]]；同时还被认为是世界舞蹈之都<ref>{{Cite web |title=capital |url=http://dictionary.reference.com/browse/capital |accessdate=2011-07-10 |publisher=Dictionary.com |archive-date=2016-03-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160306144724/http://dictionary.reference.com/browse/capital |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=Free To Dance – About The Film |url=http://www.pbs.org/wnet/freetodance/about/episodes.html |accessdate=2011-07-10 |publisher=Public Broadcasting Service |archive-date=2015-05-10 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150510053423/http://www.pbs.org/wnet/freetodance/about/episodes.html |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=Group Visits |url=http://www.alvinailey.org/about/visit-us/group-visits |accessdate=2011-07-10 |publisher=Alvin Ailey Dance Foundation, Inc |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110513030823/http://www.alvinailey.org/about/visit-us/group-visits |archivedate=2011-05-13 |deadurl=yes}}</ref>。在流行文化中纽约有极高的地位，时常成为文学、电影和电视的背景设定。

2014年美國全球語言觀察機構（GLM）公布最新調查指出，根據過去三年透過字詞使用分析趨勢，紐約擠下巴黎成為全球排名第一的時尚城市。<ref>蔡佳伶，《全球時尚霸主 紐約擠下巴黎》，中央社，2014/02/05， http://www.cna.com.tw/news/aopl/201402050452-1.aspx {{Wayback|url=http://www.cna.com.tw/news/aopl/201402050452-1.aspx |date=20140221230042 }}</ref>

=== 娛樂與表演藝術 ===
{{See also|纽约市音乐}}
[[File:Lincoln_Center_Twilight.jpg|缩略图]]是[[纽约爱乐|纽约爱乐]]等表演团体的所在地]]
纽约是美国娱乐产业的重地，许多电影、电视剧、书籍和其他媒体形式都以此处为根据地。截至2008年，紐約是美國第二大的電影中心，雇佣人数达到63,000人，总薪酬达到50亿美元<ref>{{Cite web |title=NYC Film Industry Second in Nation |url=http://www.crainsnewyork.com/article/20100316/FREE/100319919# |accessdate=2012-02-08 |author=Miriam Kreinin Souccar |publisher=Crain Communications |archive-date=2010-03-22 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100322222524/http://www.crainsnewyork.com/article/20100316/FREE/100319919 |dead-url=no }}</ref>，[[独立电影|独立电影]]出产数目居世界之冠<ref>{{Cite web |title=New York Film Academy, New York City |url=http://www.nyfa.edu/filmschools/newyork.php |accessdate=2012-02-08 |publisher=New York Film Academy |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120126210946/http://www.nyfa.edu/filmschools/newyork.php |archivedate=2012-01-26 |deadurl=yes}}</ref>。

纽约全市有2,000個以上的文化藝術組織以及超过500個不同规模的藝廊<ref name="NYC arts">{{Cite web |title=Creative New York |url=http://www.nycfuture.org/images_pdfs/pdfs/CREATIVE_NEW_YORK.pdf |accessdate=2008-09-01 |date=December 2005 |format=PDF |publisher=Center for an Urban Future |archive-date=2011-01-28 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110128170345/http://www.nycfuture.org/images_pdfs/pdfs/CREATIVE_NEW_YORK.pdf |dead-url=yes }}</ref>。纽约市市政府對藝術的資助预算超過{{Link-en|美國藝術基金會|National Endowment for the Arts}}的总预算<ref name="NYC arts" />。19世紀富有的企業家们建立了一個文化机构網絡，这其中包括[[卡內基大廳|卡內基大廳]]和[[大都会艺术博物馆|大都会艺术博物馆]]。電力照明的使用使戏剧蓬勃發展，19世纪80年代，[[百老匯|百老匯]]和[[42街|42街]]的戲院開始演出一種全新的表演形式，即[[音樂劇|音樂劇]]。受到移民文化的影响，舞台劇經常使用敘事性的歌曲，反映希望與抱負。

市内40家戏院（每家500个座位以上）共同组成了著名的[[百老汇剧院|百老汇]]，以一条穿越[[時報廣場|时代广场]][[戏院区_(曼哈顿)|戏院区]]的[[百老汇|大道]]命名<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.signonsandiego.com/news/features/20040606-9999-1a6tony.html |title=2 plays + 9 nominations=good odds for locals |author=Welsh, Anne Marie |date=2004-06-06 |publisher=San Diego Union-Tribune |accessdate=2008-09-01 |archive-date=2008-10-05 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20081005110339/http://www.signonsandiego.com/news/features/20040606-9999-1a6tony.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>，有时也被称作“大白路”（The Great White Way）<ref>McBeth, VR. [http://timessquare.com/NYC__/Times_Square_History/The_Great_White_Way/ "The Great White Way"] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110504160457/http://timessquare.com/NYC__/Times_Square_History/The_Great_White_Way/ |date=2011-05-04 }} on TimesSquare.com.  Quote: "Coined in 1901 by O.J. Gude, the designer of many prominent advertising displays, to describe the new light show that beckoned along Broadway,The Great White Way is a phrase known worldwide to describe Broadway's profusion of theaters in Times Square."</ref><ref>Tell, Darcy. [http://books.google.com/books?id=NwaLWFSG3rcC&pg=PA41&dq=%22Times+Square%22+%22Great+White+Way%22&hl=en&sa=X&ei=yHUaT4SVM6qZ0QHKpYS1Cw&ved=0CFEQ6AEwBQ#v=onepage&q=%22Times%20Square%22%20%22Great%20White%20Way%22&f=false ''Times Square spectacular: lighting up Broadway''] {{Wayback|url=http://books.google.com/books?id=NwaLWFSG3rcC&pg=PA41&dq=%22Times+Square%22+%22Great+White+Way%22&hl=en&sa=X&ei=yHUaT4SVM6qZ0QHKpYS1Cw&ved=0CFEQ6AEwBQ#v=onepage&q=%22Times%20Square%22%20%22Great%20White%20Way%22&f=false |date=20150222153201 }} New York: HarperCollins, 2007</ref><ref>Allen, Irving Lewis. [http://books.google.com/books?id=j41z0yeKbeIC&pg=PA59&dq=%22Times+Square%22+%22Great+White+Way%22&hl=en&sa=X&ei=yHUaT4SVM6qZ0QHKpYS1Cw&ved=0CFwQ6AEwBw#v=onepage&q=%22Times%20Square%22%20%22Great%20White%20Way%22&f=false ''The City in Slang: New York Life and Popular Speech''] {{Wayback|url=http://books.google.com/books?id=j41z0yeKbeIC&pg=PA59&dq=%22Times+Square%22+%22Great+White+Way%22&hl=en&sa=X&ei=yHUaT4SVM6qZ0QHKpYS1Cw&ved=0CFwQ6AEwBw#v=onepage&q=%22Times%20Square%22%20%22Great%20White%20Way%22&f=false |date=20150222104034 }}. New York: Oxford University Press, 1995.  Quote: "By 1910, the blocks of Broadway just above 42nd Street were at the very heart of the Great White Way. The glow of Times Square symbolized the center of New York, if not of the world."</ref>。

[[林肯中心|林肯中心]]是全美最大的表演藝術中心，是12個知名藝術表演組織的根据地，如[[大都會歌劇院|大都會歌劇团]]、{{Link-en|纽约市歌剧团|New York City Opera}}、[[紐約愛樂|紐約愛樂樂团]]和[[纽约市芭蕾舞团|纽约市芭蕾舞团]]等，此外{{Link-en|维维安·比蒙剧院|Vivian Beaumont Theater}}、[[朱利亚德学院|朱利亚德学院]]、{{Link-en|林肯中心爵士乐厅|Jazz at Lincoln Center}}和{{Link-en|爱丽丝·图利音乐厅|Alice Tully Hall}}也在此处。在[[联合广场_(纽约市)|联合广场]]坐落有{{Link-en|李·斯特拉斯堡戏剧和电影学院|Lee Strasberg Theatre and Film Institute}}，在[[纽约大学|纽约大学]]则有{{Link-en|帝许艺术学院|Tisch School of the Arts}}，而{{Link-en|中央公園夏日舞台|Central Park SummerStage}}则提供免費的戲劇和音樂演出<ref>{{Cite web |title=Summerstage: Our Mission |url=http://www.summerstage.org/index.aspx?lobid=854 |accessdate=2008-09-01 |publisher=Summerstage.org |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080820201634/http://www.summerstage.org/index.aspx?lobid=854 |archivedate=2008-08-20 |deadurl=yes}}</ref>。

=== 旅游 ===
{{Further|纽约市旅游业|纽约市博物馆与文化机构列表}}
[[File:1_times_square_night_2013.jpg|缩略图]]是全美乃至全世界游客最多的景点<ref>{{Cite web |title=The Crossroads of the World |url=http://pbskids.org/bigapplehistory/arts/topic15.html |accessdate=2008-01-30 |publisher=PBS |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080105113922/http://pbskids.org/bigapplehistory/arts/topic15.html |archivedate=2008-01-05 |deadurl=yes}}</ref>]]
旅游业是纽约最重要的产业之一，在过去五年内到访的国内外旅客达到年均4000万<ref name="NYC Statistics">{{Cite web |title=NYC Statistics |url=http://www.nycgo.com/?event=view.article&id=78912 |accessdate=2010-08-21 |publisher=NYC & Company |archive-date=2010-08-17 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100817142304/http://www.nycgo.com/?event=view.article&id=78912 |dead-url=no }}</ref>，最主要的旅游目的地包括[[帝国大厦|帝国大厦]]、[[自由女神像|自由女神像]]、[[埃利斯岛|埃利斯岛]]、百老汇剧院、博物馆（如[[大都会艺术博物馆|大都会艺术博物馆]]）、城市绿地（如中央公园和[[华盛顿广场公园|华盛顿广场公园]]）、[[洛克菲勒中心|洛克菲勒中心]]、时代广场、[[曼哈顿华埠|曼哈顿华埠]]及[[第五大道|第五大道]]和[[麦迪逊大道|麦迪逊大道]]的奢侈品购物游；活动还包括[[格林尼治村|格林尼治村]]的{{Link-en|纽约万圣节游行|New York's Village Halloween Parade|万圣节游行}}、[[梅西感恩节大游行|梅西的感恩节大游行]]、{{Link-en|洛克菲勒中心圣诞树|Rockefeller Center Christmas Tree}}的点亮、[[圣帕特里克节|圣帕特里克节]]游行、冬季的中央公园滑冰、[[翠贝卡电影节|翠贝卡电影节]]和中央公园的夏季表演。其他特色目的地包括[[布朗克斯动物园|布朗克斯动物园]]、[[康尼岛|康尼岛]]、[[法拉盛草原可乐娜公园|法拉盛草原可乐娜公园]]和[[纽约植物园|纽约植物园]]。前市长[[彭博|彭博]]于2012年9月27日宣布将于斯塔滕岛北岸建造世界上最大的[[摩天轮|摩天轮]]纽约轮，遥望自由女神像、纽约港和曼哈顿下城<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.nbcnews.com/travel/itineraries/nyc-get-worlds-largest-ferris-wheel-6169634 |title=NYC to get 'world's largest' Ferris wheel |author=Jennifer Peltz, Associated Press |date=2012-09-28 |publisher=NBC News |accessdate=2012-09-28 |agency=Associated Press |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120929023222/http://www.nbcnews.com/travel/itineraries/nyc-get-worlds-largest-ferris-wheel-6169634 |archivedate=2012-09-29 |dead-url=yes}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=http://cityroom.blogs.nytimes.com/2012/09/27/worlds-tallest-ferris-wheel-planned-for-staten-island/ |title=World's Tallest Ferris Wheel Planned for Staten Island |author=James Barron |date=2012-09-27 |newspaper=The New York Times |accessdate=2012-09-28 |archive-date=2012-09-29 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120929032418/http://cityroom.blogs.nytimes.com/2012/09/27/worlds-tallest-ferris-wheel-planned-for-staten-island/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

2010年纽约的游客达到4900万<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://articles.cnn.com/2011-01-04/travel/new.york.city.tourism_1_room-rates-hospitality-industry-job-data?_s=PM:TRAVEL |title=New York City draws 48.7 million tourists in 2010 |date=2011-01-04 |publisher=CNN |accessdate=2012-01-22 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120121030245/http://articles.cnn.com/2011-01-04/travel/new.york.city.tourism_1_room-rates-hospitality-industry-job-data?_s=PM:TRAVEL |archivedate=2012-01-21 |dead-url=yes}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=NYC The Official Guide nycgo.com – nyc statistics |url=http://www.nycgo.com/articles/nyc-statistics-page |accessdate=2012-01-22 |publisher=NYC & Company, Inc |archive-date=2011-05-05 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110505004453/http://www.nycgo.com/articles/nyc-statistics-page |dead-url=no }}</ref>，而在次年这一纪录立刻被打破，2011年游客达到5000万<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://cityroom.blogs.nytimes.com/2011/12/20/as-city-closes-in-on-50-millionth-visitor-british-couple-to-be-feted/?scp=1&sq=tourists&st=Search |title=As City Closes In on 50 Millionth Visitor, British Couple to Be Feted |author=Patrick McGeehan |date=2011-12-20 |publisher=The New York Times |accessdate=2012-01-22 |archive-date=2012-01-18 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120118111933/http://cityroom.blogs.nytimes.com/2011/12/20/as-city-closes-in-on-50-millionth-visitor-british-couple-to-be-feted/?scp=1&sq=tourists&st=Search |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=NYC reaches goal of 50 million tourists |url=http://www.northjersey.com/news/135934558_NYC_reaches_goal_of_50_million_tourists.html |accessdate=2012-01-22 |date=2011-12-20 |publisher=North Jersey Media Group |archive-date=2013-07-23 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130723014600/http://www.northjersey.com/news/135934558_NYC_reaches_goal_of_50_million_tourists.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

=== 媒體 ===
{{Main|纽约市媒体}}
[[File:Rockefeller_Center_(2006).JPG|缩略图]]的[[國家廣播公司|國家廣播公司]]制片部]]
紐約為全球電視、廣告、音樂、報紙和圖書出版業的重鎮，亦是北美最大的媒體市場（其次為[[洛杉磯|洛杉磯]]、[[芝加哥|芝加哥]]和[[多倫多|多倫多]]）<ref>{{Cite press release |title=Tampa Bay 12th largest media market now |publisher=Tampa Bay Partnership |date=2006-08-26 |url=http://www.tampabay.org/press.asp?rls_id=991& |accessdate=2008-09-01 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080928205103/http://www.tampabay.org/press.asp?rls_id=991& |archivedate=2008-09-28}}</ref>。知名的媒體企業包括[[時代華納|時代華納]]、[[汤森路透公司|汤森路透公司]]、[[美国联合通讯社|美国联合通讯社]]、[[新闻集团_(1979－2013年)|新闻集团]]、[[纽约时报公司|纽约时报公司]]、[[NBC环球|NBC环球]]、[[赫斯特國際集團|赫斯特國際集團]]和[[維亞康姆|維亞康姆]]。全球前八大的廣告媒體就有七家在紐約市設立總部<ref>[http://adage.com/datacenter/datapopup.php?article_id=116384 Top 10 Consolidated Agency Networks: Ranked by 2006 Worldwide Network Revenue] {{Wayback|url=http://adage.com/datacenter/datapopup.php?article_id=116384 |date=20070503025443 }}, ''{{tsl|en|Advertising Age||Advertising Age}}'' Agency Report 2007 Index (April 25, 2007). Retrieved on June 8, 2007.</ref>。全球[[音乐产业|三大唱片公司]]中有两家（[[索尼音乐娱乐|索尼音乐娱乐]]及[[华纳音乐集团|华纳音乐集团]]）将总部设在纽约，而第三家（[[环球唱片|环球唱片]]）在纽约也设有分公司。1/3的美國[[獨立電影|獨立電影]]在紐約製作<ref name="NYC Media">{{Cite web |title=Request for Expressions of Interest |url=http://www.govisland.com/PDFs/RFEI/RFEI.pdf |accessdate=2008-09-01 |year=2005 |format=PDF |publisher=The Governors Island Preservation & Education Corporation |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080802030053/http://www.govisland.com/PDFs/RFEI/RFEI.pdf |archivedate=2008-08-02 |deadurl=yes}}</ref>。

[[File:NYC_subway_riders_with_their_newspapers.jpg|缩略图]]帶動了大量的報紙讀者<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.nytimes.com/2005/12/26/business/media/26commute.html |title=Since Riders had no Subways, Commuter Papers Struggled, Too |author=Ivry, Sara |date=2005-12-26 |publisher=The New York Times |accessdate=2008-09-01 |archive-date=2009-04-15 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090415232121/http://www.nytimes.com/2005/12/26/business/media/26commute.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>]]
超過200種報紙和350種雜誌在纽约設有辦公室<ref name="NYC Media" />，圖書出版業提供了25,000个就业岗位<ref>{{Cite web |title=Media and Entertainment |url=http://www.nycedc.com/Web/NYCBusinessClimate/IndustryOverviews/MediaEntertainment/MediaEntertainment.htm |accessdate=2008-09-01 |publisher=New York City Economic Development Corporation |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080128210353/http://www.nycedc.com/Web/NYCBusinessClimate/IndustryOverviews/MediaEntertainment/MediaEntertainment.htm |archivedate=2008-01-28 |deadurl=yes}}</ref>。美国三大全国性日报中有两大在纽约出版，分别为《[[紐約時報|紐約時報]]》和《[[華爾街日報|華爾街日報]]》，其中前者在[[普利策奖|普利策奖]]数目上高居第一。其他小報包括1919年创办的《[[纽约每日新闻|纽约每日新闻]]》<ref>{{Cite web |title=New York Daily News (American newspaper) |url=http://www.britannica.com/EBchecked/topic/412434/New-York-Daily-News |accessdate=2013-05-04 |publisher=Britannica.com |archive-date=2015-04-30 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150430133613/http://www.britannica.com/EBchecked/topic/412434/New-York-Daily-News |dead-url=no }}</ref>和1801年创办的《[[紐約郵報|紐約郵報]]》<ref>Allan Nevins, ''The Evening Post: Century of Journalism'', Boni and Liveright, 1922, page 17.</ref>。此外在不同族裔出版业方面纽约也相当多元化，有270份报章杂志以超过40种语言版本出版<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.editorandpublisher.com/eandp/news/article_display.jsp?vnu_content_id=1538594 |title=Ethnic Press Booms In New York City |date=2002-07-10 |publisher=Editor & Publisher |accessdate=2008-09-01 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20060205114424/http://www.editorandpublisher.com/eandp/news/article_display.jsp?vnu_content_id=1538594 |archivedate=2006-02-05 |dead-url=yes}}</ref>，其中《{{lang|es|El Diario La Prensa}}》是全纽约发行量最大及全国历史最悠久的[[西班牙语|西班牙语]]报纸<ref>{{Cite web |title=el Diario/La Prensa: The Nation's Oldest Spanish-Language Daily |url=http://news.newamericamedia.org/news/view_article.html?article_id=e4526a43cc213775795cc84762fce768 |accessdate=2008-09-01 |date=2005-07-27 |publisher=New America Media |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080522105604/http://news.newamericamedia.org/news/view_article.html?article_id=e4526a43cc213775795cc84762fce768 |archivedate=2008-05-22 |deadurl=yes}}</ref>，出版于哈莱姆的《{{Link-en|纽约阿姆斯特丹新闻|The New York Amsterdam News}}》是一份重要的非裔美国人报纸。《{{link-en|鄉村之音|The Village Voice}}》是全美發行量最大的另类报纸，專門報導時事評論以及特色主題。

電視產業對於紐約來說是相當重要的經濟命脈。美国四大廣播公司，包括[[美國廣播公司|美國廣播公司]]、[[哥倫比亞廣播公司|哥倫比亞廣播公司]]、[[福克斯廣播公司|福克斯廣播公司]]和[[國家廣播公司|國家廣播公司]]，都在紐約設立總部。此外，一些如[[音樂電視網|音樂電視網]]、[[HBO|HBO]]、[[福克斯新聞頻道|福克斯新聞頻道]]和[[喜剧中心|喜剧中心]]等有線電視頻道也将总部设在此地。2005年，有超過100個電視節目在紐約拍攝<ref>{{Cite press release |title=2005 is banner year for production in New York |publisher=The City of New York Mayor's Office of Film, Theater and Broadcasting |date=2005-12-28 |url=http://www.nyc.gov/html/film/html/news/010106_2005_banner_year.shtml |accessdate=2008-09-01 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://archive.is/20120526195430/http://www.nyc.gov/html/film/html/news/010106_2005_banner_year.shtml |archivedate=2012-05-26}}</ref>。纽约市也经营了一个公共广播频道{{Link-en|NYCTV|nyctv}}，多次夺得[[艾美獎|艾美獎]]，節目內容大多涵蓋紐約市內的音樂、文化以及政府相關活動。

除了商業媒體之外，紐約也是非商業媒體的的中心。1971年創立的{{link-en|曼哈頓公共電視網|Manhattan Neighborhood Network}}是美國歷史最悠久的{{Link-en|公共頻道|public-access television}}<ref>[http://www.mnn.org/en/community-celebrates-public-access-tvs-35th-annive Community Celebrates Public Access TV's 35th Anniversary] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070904054553/http://www.mnn.org/en/community-celebrates-public-access-tvs-35th-annive |date=2007-09-04 }}, {{tsl|en|Manhattan Neighborhood Network||Manhattan Neighborhood Network}} press release dated August 6, 2006. Accessed April 28, 2007. "Public access TV was created in the 1970s to allow ordinary members of the public to make and air their own TV shows—and thereby exercise their free speech. It was first launched in the U.S. in Manhattan July 1, 1971, on the Teleprompter and Sterling Cable systems, now Time Warner Cable."</ref>。{{Link-en|WNET|WNET}}是紐約最大的公共電視台，也是全國[[公共電視網|公共電視網]]的主要節目提供者。{{Link-en|WNYC|WNYC}}是全美最多聽眾收聽的公共广播電台<ref>{{Cite web |title=Top 30 Public Radio Subscribers: Spring 2006 Arbitron |url=http://www.rrconline.org/reports/pdf/Sp06%20eRanks.pdf |accessdate=2008-09-01 |date=2006-08-28 |format=PDF |publisher=Radio Research Consortium |archive-date=2013-01-13 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130113222054/http://www.rrconline.org/reports/pdf/Sp06%20eRanks.pdf |dead-url=yes }}</ref>。

=== 飲食 ===
{{Main|纽约市饮食}}
[[File:Serendipity_3.jpg|缩略图]]是[[曼哈顿|曼哈顿]]一家广受欢迎的餐馆，由史蒂芬·布鲁斯创立于1954年<ref>{{Cite web |title=Serendipity 3 |url=http://www.serendipity3.com/history.htm |accessdate=2009-03-10 |dead-url=yes |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090319023314/http://www.serendipity3.com/history.htm |archive-date=2009-03-19}}</ref>]]
纽约的饮食文化受其移民历史的影响，呈多元化态势，包括的国际餐点十分众多。[[中欧|中欧]]和[[意大利|意大利]]移民带来了纽约极富盛名的[[贝果|贝果]]、[[起士蛋糕|起士蛋糕]]和[[纽约式披萨|纽约式披萨]]，而中国和其他亚洲餐馆、汉堡店、{{Link-en|意式饮食店|Trattoria}}、{{Link-en|餐车餐厅|Diner}}和咖啡屋随处可见。市内有约4,000个拥有执照的小吃摊点，许多都由移民经营，[[中东|中东]]食物诸如[[炸豆丸子|炸豆丸子]]和[[卡博串|卡博串]]便是广受欢迎的纽约[[街头食品|街头食品]]的代表<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.nytimes.com/2006/05/14/nyregion/thecity/14vend.html |title=Kebabs on the Night Shift |last=Bleyer |first=Jennifer |date=2006-05-14 |work=The New York Times |accessdate=2014-01-17 |archive-date=2009-04-15 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090415232123/http://www.nytimes.com/2006/05/14/nyregion/thecity/14vend.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>。同时，纽约还是许多全美国最好和最多元的高档餐厅的聚集地<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://query.nytimes.com/gst/fullpage.html?res=9C03E0D9163EF930A35752C1A9639C8B63 |title=Michelin Takes on the City, Giving Some a Bad Taste |last=Collins |first=Glenn |date=2005-11-03 |work=The New York Times |accessdate=2006-07-19 |archive-date=2017-09-05 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170905142244/http://query.nytimes.com/gst/fullpage.html?res=9C03E0D9163EF930A35752C1A9639C8B63 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。{{Link-en|纽约市健康与精神卫生局|New York City Department of Health and Mental Hygiene}}根据其检测结果对纽约市近24,000家餐馆进行等级评定。
=== 方言 ===
{{Main|纽约方言}}
纽约方言有鲜明的地域特征，被普遍认为是美式英语中最知名的口音之一。方言经典版本以欧洲人后裔和工薪阶层为中心，而几十年来非欧洲移民的大量涌入，促使这门独特的方言产生改变。传统纽约方言发音时无需翘首，音节末尾不带辅音，使得该方言中的“纽约”听起来像“New Yawk”。最为地道的和极限版的纽约方言发音，单元音变成双元音，如“女孩”。上世纪70年代电视剧《[[一家子|一家子]]》中[[卡罗尔·奥康纳|卡罗尔·奥康纳]]扮演的阿尔奇·邦克就是这种发音模式，但往后这种发音逐渐淡出人们的视野。

