{{Main|纽约市政府}}
[[File:Municipal_Building_-_New_York_City.jpg|缩略图]]是许多市政府部门的办公地点]]
自1898年合并建市以来，纽约市便采用[[市长议会制政府|市长议会制]]的政府组织形式<ref>{{Cite web |title=Forms of Municipal Government |url=http://www.nlc.org/build-skills-networks/resources/cities-101/forms-of-municipal-government |accessdate=2012-02-10 |publisher=National League of Cities |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120118035924/http://www.nlc.org/build-skills-networks/resources/cities-101/forms-of-municipal-government |archivedate=2012-01-18 |deadurl=yes}}</ref>。纽约市政府要比美国其他城市的政府权力更为集中，负责公共教育、惩教机构、图书馆、公共安全、娱乐设施、环境卫生、供水和福利服务。[[纽约市市长|市长]]和市议会议员由选举产生，任期四年。[[纽约市议会|纽约市议会]]采取[[一院制|一院制]]，议员共51人，来自根据地理位置划分的不同选区<ref>{{Cite web |title=About the Council |url=http://www.nyccouncil.info/html/actioncenter/moved.cfm |accessdate=2007-06-06 |publisher=New York City Council |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20071208230244/http://www.nyccouncil.info/html/actioncenter/moved.cfm |archivedate=2007-12-08 |deadurl=yes}}</ref>。市长最多能够连任二届，议员最多能够连任三届<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://cityroom.blogs.nytimes.com/2008/10/23/council-to-debate-term-limits-change/ |title=Council Votes, 29 to 22, to Extend Term Limits |author=Sewell Chan and Jonathan P. Hicks |date=2008-10-23 |newspaper=The New York Times |accessdate=2012-02-13 |archive-date=2011-02-28 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110228131857/http://cityroom.blogs.nytimes.com/2008/10/23/council-to-debate-term-limits-change/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>，但在中断四年之后可以重新参选。
[[File:New_York_City_Hall.jpg|缩略图]]是全美最老的仍在行使政府职责的市政厅]]

现任纽约市长为[[比尔·白思豪|比尔·白思豪]]，[[民主党_(美国)|民主党人]]<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.nytimes.com/2013/11/06/nyregion/de-blasio-is-elected-new-york-city-mayor.html?_r=0 |title=De Blasio Is Elected New York City Mayor |author=Michael Barbaro and David W. Chen |date=2013-11-05 |newspaper=The New York Times |accessdate=2013-11-06 |archive-date=2021-04-17 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210417165650/https://www.nytimes.com/2013/11/06/nyregion/de-blasio-is-elected-new-york-city-mayor.html?_r=0 |dead-url=no }}</ref>，2014年1月1日就职。過去20年紐約市由共和黨主政，[[魯迪·朱利安尼|魯迪·朱利安尼]]及[[米高·彭博|米高·彭博]]<ref>彭博於2007年轉為無黨派人士，但2009年仍代表共和黨參選並成功連任。</ref>先後成為紐約市長，在任期間大幅改善紐約市的治安及環境。

民主党占有大部分的公职。至2008年11月，67%的注册选民为民主党人<ref>{{Cite web |title=NYSVoter Enrollment by County, Party Affiliation and Status |url=http://www.elections.ny.gov/NYSBOE/enrollment/county/county_nov08.pdf |accessdate=2009-02-08 |date=November 2008 |publisher=New York State Board of Elections |archive-date=2021-04-22 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210422042639/https://www.elections.ny.gov/NYSBOE/enrollment/county/county_nov08.pdf |dead-url=no }}</ref>。自1924年以来，共和党从来没有在州选举或总统选举中在纽约市取得胜利。纽约的[[政纲|政党纲领]]主要涉及保障性住房、教育和经济发展问题，劳工问题也是十分重要的一个政治议题。

1975年，在经历财政危机和州政府救助之后，纽约市财政控制委员会建立起来以监督市政支出。委员会由七人组成，其中包括纽约市市长和纽约州州长<ref>{{Cite web |title=Financial Control Board |url=http://www.fcb.state.ny.us/members.asp |accessdate=2013-10-24 |publisher=State of New York |archive-date=2021-04-21 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210421010416/http://www.fcb.state.ny.us/members.asp |dead-url=no }}</ref>。1986年这一委员会不再直接管理市政预算，但它仍然保有监控市财政健康状况的指责<ref>{{Cite web |title=New York State Financial Control Board |url=http://www.fcb.state.ny.us/ |accessdate=2012-05-28 |archive-date=2021-04-21 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210421000210/http://www.fcb.state.ny.us/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

纽约市是全美最重要的[[政治献金|政治献金]]获取地，五个全国政治献金最高的[[美国邮政编码|邮政编码]]归属地有四个位于曼哈顿，其中最高者是位于[[上东城|上东城]]的10021号，这一编码区为2004年总统选举候选人[[乔治·沃克·布什|乔治·W·布什]]和[[约翰·福布斯·克里|约翰·克里]]提供了大部分的选举资金<ref>{{Cite web |title=2006 Election Overview: Top Zip Codes |url=http://www.opensecrets.org/overview/topzips.php?cycle=2004 |accessdate=2008-09-01 |publisher=Opensecrets.org |archive-date=2020-07-25 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200725113913/http://www.opensecrets.org/overview/topzips.php?cycle=2004 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。在联邦和州税方面纽约存在着很大的顺差：每向联邦政府上缴1美元的税收，收回83美分的联邦服务（即每年上缴比获取多114亿美元）；每年向州政府上缴的也比获取的多110亿美元<ref>{{Cite web |title=A Fair Share of State Budget: Does Albany Play Fair with NYC? |url=http://webdocs.nyccouncil.info/attachments/65379.htm?CFID=232457&CFTOKEN=33008944 |accessdate=2008-09-01 |date=2005-03-11 |publisher=New York City Finance Division |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080525082617/http://webdocs.nyccouncil.info/attachments/65379.htm?CFID=232457&CFTOKEN=33008944 |archivedate=2008-05-25 |deadurl=yes}}</ref>。

每个行政区同时也是[[纽约最高法院|纽约最高法院]]的一个司法辖区，同时也受理其他城市和其他州法庭的事务。曼哈顿和布鲁克林分别是[[纽约最高法院上诉法院|纽约最高法院上诉法院]]第一和第二区的总部所在地<ref name="AD">[http://www.nycourts.gov/courts/appellatedivisions.shtml NY Courts website Appellate Divisions page] {{Wayback|url=http://www.nycourts.gov/courts/appellatedivisions.shtml |date=20210424181557 }}.  Accessed 2009-06-24.</ref>。与其他大城市不同的是，纽约被分归两个[[美国联邦地区法院|美国联邦地区法院]]管辖（同时也是两个地区法院的所在地）：[[美国纽约南区联邦地区法院|美国纽约南区联邦地区法院]]，位于市政厅附近的[[弗利广场|弗利广场]]，管辖曼哈顿和布朗克斯；[[美国纽约东区联邦地区法院|美国纽约东区联邦地区法院]]，位于布鲁克林，管辖布鲁克林、皇后区和斯塔滕岛。[[美国联邦第二巡回上诉法院|美国联邦第二巡回上诉法院]]和[[美国国际贸易法院|美国国际贸易法院]]同样位于曼哈顿的弗利广场。

=== 環境 ===
{{Further|纽约市环境问题|纽约市食品和水源}}
紐約的公共交通使用率為全美最高，汽油消耗量与1920年代全美平均水平相近<ref name="NYC energy consumption">{{Cite book |title=The Big Green Apple: Your Guide to Eco-Friendly Living in New York City |last=Jervey |first=Ben |publisher=Globe Pequot Press |year=2006 |isbn=0762738359}}</ref>。據2006年統計，其極高的公共交通使用率在當年就省下了18亿美制加仑（6,800,000立方米）的石油消耗量，光是紐約市省下的油量就達到是全美公共交通省油量的一半<ref>{{Cite web |title=A Better Way to Go: Meeting America's 21st Century Transportation Challenges with Modern Public Transit |url=http://www.uspirg.org/uploads/2q/fV/2qfVu2ZrflTk-TnRQEDdDw/A-Better-Way-to-Go-vUSPIRG.pdf |accessdate=2008-04-23 |date=March 2008 |format=PDF |publisher=U.S. Public Interest Research Group |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080516180756/http://www.uspirg.org/uploads/2q/fV/2qfVu2ZrflTk-TnRQEDdDw/A-Better-Way-to-Go-vUSPIRG.pdf |archivedate=2008-05-16 |deadurl=yes}}</ref>。紐約市人口密度高，公共交通使用率高，汽車使用率低，使得之成為全美最節能的城市之一<ref>{{Cite news |title=Green Manhattan |author=Owen, David |date=2004-10-18 |publisher=The New Yorker}}</ref>。人均[[溫室氣體|溫室氣體]]排放量只有7.1[[公噸|公噸]]，與全美平均24.5公噸相較起來要低很多<ref name="NYC emissions" />，全市人口數雖佔全國人口2.7%，但溫室氣體排放量只佔全國排放量的百分之一<ref name="NYC emissions">{{Cite web |title=Inventory of New York City Greenhouse Gas Emissions |url=http://www.nyc.gov/html/om/pdf/ccp_report041007.pdf |accessdate=2008-09-01 |date=April 2007 |format=PDF |publisher=New York City Office of Long-term Planning and Sustainability |archive-date=2011-07-21 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110721185837/http://www.nyc.gov/html/om/pdf/ccp_report041007.pdf |dead-url=no }}</ref>，紐約居民所耗費的電量比[[舊金山|舊金山]]居民耗費量的一半還少，是[[達拉斯|達拉斯]]居民的近四分之一<ref>{{Cite web |title=Global Warming and Greenhouse Gases |url=http://www.nyc.gov/html/planyc2030/html/challenge/faq.shtml |accessdate=2008-09-01 |date=2006-12-06 |publisher={{tsl|en|PlaNYC||PlaNYC}}/The City of New York |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20101225070759/http://www.nyc.gov/html/planyc2030/html/challenge/faq.shtml |archivedate=2010-12-25 |deadurl=yes}}</ref>。

[[File:NYC_Hybrid_Taxi.JPG|缩略图]]計程車投入營運，数量为北美最多]]
近年來，紐約市開始實施計畫欲減低对環境的衝擊。市内大量且集中的空氣污染导致[[氣喘|氣喘]]和其他呼吸道疾病在纽约市民身上的發生率较高<ref>{{Cite journal |title=Urban Asthma and the Neighbourhood Environment in New York City |author=Coburn, Jason, Jeffrey Osleeb, Michael Porter |date=June 2006 |journal=Health & Place |issue=2 |doi=10.1016/j.healthplace.2004.11.002 |volume=12 |pages=167–179 |pmid=16338632}}</ref>。市政府被要求只能采购最節能的設備，以供市政府辦公室和公共住宅使用<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.nytimes.com/2005/12/11/nyregion/11efficiency.html |title=It Never Sleeps, but It's Learned to Douse the Lights |author=DePalma, Anthony |date=2005-12-11 |publisher=The New York Times |accessdate=2008-09-01 |archive-date=2009-04-15 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090415232102/http://www.nytimes.com/2005/12/11/nyregion/11efficiency.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>。此外，纽约有全国最多的使用清洁空气柴油[[混合動力車輛|混合動力]]和[[壓縮天然氣|壓縮天然氣]]的公車<ref>{{Cite web |title=A Century of Buses in New York City |url=http://www.mta.info/nyct/bus/centennial/page2.htm |accessdate=2008-09-01 |publisher=Metropolitan Transportation Authority |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20060525043420/http://mta.info/nyct/bus/centennial/page2.htm |archivedate=2006-05-25 |deadurl=yes}} See also {{cite press release |url=http://www.sierraclub.org/pressroom/releases/pr2005-07-01a.asp |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080418021037/http://www.sierraclub.org/pressroom/releases/pr2005-07-01a.asp |archivedate=2008-04-18 |title=New York City's Yellow Cabs Go Green |publisher=Sierra Club |date=2005-07-01 |accessdate=2008-09-01 |deadurl=yes }}</ref>，至2010年中有3,715輛混和動力計程車和[[超低硫柴油|清洁柴油]]車輛，佔全市計程車輛總數的28%，位居北美第一<ref name="NYT072710">{{Cite news |url=http://cityroom.blogs.nytimes.com/2010/07/27/appeals-court-rejects-effort-to-create-hybrid-taxi-fleet/?emc=eta1 |title=Appeals Court Rejects Effort to Create Hybrid Taxi Fleet |last=Newman |first=Andy |date=2010-07-27 |publisher=New York Times |accessdate=2010-07-31 |archive-date=2011-08-15 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110815113826/http://cityroom.blogs.nytimes.com/2010/07/27/appeals-court-rejects-effort-to-create-hybrid-taxi-fleet/?emc=eta1 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

紐約市政府曾在{{Link-en|马萨诸塞州诉美国国家环境保护局案|Massachusetts v. Environmental Protection Agency}}中發起訴願，要求[[美國國家環境保護局|美國國家環境保護局]]將溫室氣體歸類为汙染物，此外市政府也主導[[綠色建築|綠色建築]]的興建，如[[赫斯特大樓|赫斯特大樓]]<ref name="greenbuilding">{{Cite news |url=http://www.nytimes.com/2006/04/16/arts/design/16gree.html |title=7 World Trade Center and Hearst Building: New York's Test Cases for Environmentally Aware Office Towers |author=Pogrebin, Robin |date=2006-04-16 |publisher=The New York Times |accessdate=2008-09-01 |archive-date=2010-11-27 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20101127121253/http://www.nytimes.com/2006/04/16/arts/design/16gree.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

紐約市內的飲用水由[[卡茲奇山|卡茲奇山]][[流域|流域]]保护区供應<ref>{{Cite web |title=Current Reservoir Levels |url=http://www.nyc.gov/html/dep/html/maplevels.html |accessdate=2007-06-04 |publisher=New York City Department of Environmental Protection |archive-date=2011-07-22 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110722020721/http://www.nyc.gov/html/dep/html/maplevels.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>，由於該地區水源得到保护较好，自然过滤系统完整，纽约成为全美四个不須經過[[水處理|水處理]]即可配送饮用水的大城市之一<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.nysun.com/new-york/citys-drinking-water-feared-endangered-10b-cost/83288/ |title=City's Drinking Water Feared Endangered; $10B Cost Seen |author=Lustgarten, Abrahm |date=2008-08-06 |publisher=The New York Sun |accessdate=2008-08-09 |archive-date=2021-05-01 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210501100413/https://www.nysun.com/new-york/citys-drinking-water-feared-endangered-10b-cost/83288/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

=== 治安 ===
{{main|纽约市治安}}
[[File:Chevrolet_Volt_NYPD_--_04-04-2012.JPG|缩略图]]
[[纽约市警察局|纽约市警察局]]有正式警员35,000人，数目在美国高居第一<ref>{{Cite web |title=Bureau of Justice Statistics - Appendix Table 1 - page 34 |url=http://www.bjs.gov/content/pub/pdf/lpd07.pdf |accessdate=2013-12-05 |publisher=U.S. Department of Justice |archive-date=2020-01-18 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200118002615/https://www.bjs.gov/content/pub/pdf/lpd07.pdf |dead-url=no }}</ref>。2012年，在全美大城市中，纽约的犯罪率为最低，谋杀率则为第二低<ref>{{Cite web |title=NYC The Safest Big City In The Country? FBI Crime Stats Mixed |url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2013/06/14/fbi-crime-stats-mixed-for_n_3439629.html |accessdate=2013-10-24 |author=Anthony M. Destefano |date=2013-06-14 |publisher=The Huffington Post (source Newsday) |archive-date=2018-03-17 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180317052059/https://www.huffingtonpost.com/2013/06/14/fbi-crime-stats-mixed-for_n_3439629.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>，与1980年代和1990年代的犯罪高潮期相比要安全了许多<ref name="Prager">Arthur Prager, [http://www.americanheritage.com/content/worst-case-scenario "Worst-Case Scenario"] {{Wayback|url=http://www.americanheritage.com/content/worst-case-scenario |date=20130330060030 }}, ''American Heritage'', February/March 2006.</ref>。至2002年，纽约的犯罪率与犹他州的[[普若佛|普若佛]]相当，在全美人口超过100,000的216座城市中排名第197<ref name="Law" />。

1993年至2005年间，纽约的暴力犯罪数量下降了75%，并且在全国水平上升的同时保持持续下降<ref name="Law">{{Cite web |title=Don't Tell New York, But Crime Is Going Up |url=http://www.lib.jjay.cuny.edu/len/2002/12.31/page5.html |accessdate=2011-08-20 |publisher=Lib.jjay.cuny.edu |archive-date=2021-10-23 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211023100612/https://www.lib.jjay.cuny.edu/len/2002/12.31/page5.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>。2005年，纽约的[[各国谋杀率列表|谋杀率]]达到了自1966年来的最低点<ref>{{Cite web |title=The Remarkable Drop in Crime in New York City |url=http://www.istat.it/istat/eventi/2003/perunasocieta/relazioni/Langan_rel.pdf |accessdate=2009-02-08 |date=2004-10-21 |last=Langan |first=Patrick A. |coauthors=Matthew R. Durose |publisher=Istituto Nazionale di Statistica |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151212083716/http://www3.istat.it/istat/eventi/2003/perunasocieta/relazioni/Langan_rel.pdf |archivedate=2015-12-12 |deadurl=yes}}</ref>，而在2007年，纽约的谋杀案件数量少于500起，这是自1963年公开犯罪数据以来首次达到这一水平<ref>[http://www.nytimes.com/2008/01/01/nyregion/01murder.html?_r=2&scp=2&sq=murder+in+2007&oref=slogin Fewer Killings in 2007, but Still Felt in City's Streets] {{Wayback|url=http://www.nytimes.com/2008/01/01/nyregion/01murder.html?_r=2&scp=2&sq=murder+in+2007&oref=slogin |date=20210417165843 }}, ''[[纽约时报|The New York Times]]'', January 1, 2008. Retrieved June 21, 2009.</ref>。2010年上半年，95.1%的谋杀案受害者和95.9%的枪击案受害者为黑人或拉丁裔，此外90.2%因谋杀被捕的和96.7%因枪击被捕的人为黑人或拉丁裔<ref>"[http://voices.washingtonpost.com/postpartisan/2010/11/post_9.html The Color of Murder and Gun Violence in New York] {{Wayback|url=http://voices.washingtonpost.com/postpartisan/2010/11/post_9.html |date=20121008064404 }}". The Washington Post. November 10, 2010</ref>。2013年纽约的谋杀率达到了新低，并远低于美国其他大城市<ref>{{Cite web |title=Mayor Bloomberg and Police Commissioner Kelly Announce 2013 Saw the Fewest Murders and Fewest Shootings in Recorded City History at NYPD Graduation Ceremony |url=http://www1.nyc.gov/office-of-the-mayor/news/436-13/mayor-bloomberg-police-commissioner-kelly-2013-saw-fewest-murders-fewest/#/0.html |access-date=2014-01-27 |archive-date=2021-04-17 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210417165855/https://www1.nyc.gov/office-of-the-mayor/news/436-13/mayor-bloomberg-police-commissioner-kelly-2013-saw-fewest-murders-fewest/#/0.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>。2012年，纽约市警察局的盘查搜身策略受到了争议<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2012/05/13/nypd-stop-and-frisks-15-shocking-facts_n_1513362.html |title=NYPD Stop And Frisks: 15 Shocking Facts About A Controversial Program |date=2012-05-15 |newspaper=Huffington Post |accessdate=2013-12-24 |archive-date=2018-09-28 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180928125848/https://www.huffingtonpost.com/2012/05/13/nypd-stop-and-frisks-15-shocking-facts_n_1513362.html |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=Stop-and-Frisk Campaign: About the Issue |url=http://www.nyclu.org/issues/racial-justice/stop-and-frisk-practices |accessdate=2013-12-24 |publisher=NYCLU |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131230180424/http://www.nyclu.org/issues/racial-justice/stop-and-frisk-practices |archivedate=2013-12-30 |deadurl=yes}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=NYPD Stop and Frisk |url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/tag/nypd-stop-and-frisk |accessdate=2013-12-24 |publisher=Huffington Post |archive-date=2015-01-04 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150104193027/http://www.huffingtonpost.com/tag/nypd-stop-and-frisk |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

社會學家和犯罪學家目前對於犯罪率大幅下降的原因還未达成共識。有些人認為原因是[[紐約市警察局|紐約市警察局]]所採取的新策略<ref>"[http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/uknews/1318236/Livingstone-to-follow-methods-of-the-NYPD.html Livingstone to follow methods of the NYPD] {{Wayback|url=http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/uknews/1318236/Livingstone-to-follow-methods-of-the-NYPD.html |date=20210417165914 }}". Telegraph. January 17, 2001.</ref>，例如電腦輔助的{{Link-en|CompStat|CompStat}}犯罪處理系統以及[[破窗效應|破窗效應理论]]的运用<ref>"[http://www.theage.com.au/articles/2002/11/02/1036027090656.html Staying a beat ahead of crime] {{Wayback|url=http://www.theage.com.au/articles/2002/11/02/1036027090656.html |date=20121104194258 }}". Theage.com.au. November 5, 2002.</ref>。其他人則認為是因為[[霹靂可卡因|霹靂可卡因]]热潮的消退及人口結構的改變<ref>{{Cite book |title=The Crime Drop in America |last=Johnson, Bruce D., Andrew Golub, Eloise Dunlap |publisher=Cambridge University Press |year=2006 |isbn=0521862795 |editor-last=Blumstein, Alfred, Joel Wallman |chapter=The Rise and Decline of Hard Drugs, Drug Markets, and Violence in Inner-City New York}}; {{Cite book|title=New York Murder Mystery: The True Story Behind the Crime Crash of the 1990s |author=Karmen, Andrew |year=2000 |publisher=NYU Press |isbn=0814747175}}</ref>。还有人认为上世纪中期的犯罪潮源自汽车尾气排放造成的铅污染导致智力水平的降低和侵略性的增强，而纽约这样的大城市受其影响最严重。1970年代，铅从美国汽油中退出，纽约和其他大城市的暴力犯罪率开始普遍下降<ref>{{Cite web |title=America's Real Criminal Element: Lead |url=http://www.motherjones.com/environment/2013/01/lead-crime-link-gasoline?page=1 |accessdate=2013-03-03 |date=January/February 2013 |last=Drum |first=Kevin |publisher=Mother Jones |archive-date=2016-01-14 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160114163430/http://www.motherjones.com/environment/2013/01/lead-crime-link-gasoline?page=1 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

[[有组织犯罪|有组织犯罪]]长期都是纽约的一大问题，1820年代即在曼哈顿五岔路出现了{{Link-en|四十大盗 (纽约黑帮)|Forty Thieves (New York gang)|四十大盗}}和{{Link-en|蟑螂卫队|Roach Guards}}这样的团伙。20世纪由[[五大家族|五大家族]]主宰的[[美国黑手党|黑手党]]崛起，至今仍是当地规模最大和最有权势的犯罪组织<ref>{{Cite book |title=NYPD: A City and Its Police |last=Lardner, James, and Thomas Reppetto |publisher=Owl Books |year=2000 |isbn=0-8050-5578-9 |pages=18–21}}</ref>。20世纪末崛起的还有{{Link-en|黑桃帮|Black Spades}}一类的黑帮团伙<ref>"[http://www.gothamgazette.com/article/issueoftheweek/20010305/200/161 Youth Gangs] {{Wayback|url=http://www.gothamgazette.com/article/issueoftheweek/20010305/200/161 |date=20120516010556 }}". {{tsl|en|Gotham Gazette||Gotham Gazette}}. March 5, 2001.</ref>。早至1850年，纽约便有超过200次帮派战争，主要在青年黑帮间进行<ref>[http://findarticles.com/p/articles/mi_m2248/is_n118_v30/ai_17150109/ "19th century AD."] {{webarchive|url=https://archive.is/20120524000955/findarticles.com/p/articles/mi_m2248/is_n118_v30/ai_17150109/ |date=2012-05-24 }} ''Adolescence'', Summer, 1995 by Ruskin Teeter.</ref>。如今纽约最知名的黑帮包括{{Link-en|Bloods|Bloods}}、{{Link-en|Crips|Crips}}、{{Link-en|拉丁国王 (黑帮)|Latin Kings (gang)|拉丁国王}}和[[MS-13|MS-13]]<ref>"[http://www.pubadvocate.nyc.gov/policy/documents/WorkingPaperonGangs1.pdf Old Problem, New Eyes: Youth Insights on Gangs in New York City] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080917134708/http://www.pubadvocate.nyc.gov/policy/documents/WorkingPaperonGangs1.pdf |date=2008-09-17 }}" (PDF). {{tsl|en|New York City Public Advocate||Public Advocate for the City of New York}}. November 2007.</ref>。

== 交通 ==
{{main|紐約交通}}
[[File:Image-Grand_central_Station_Outside_Night_2.jpg|缩略图]]的所在地，其中就包括[[大中央车站|大中央车站]]]]

[[纽约市公共交通|纽约的公共交通系统]]多为24小时营运，为全美最复杂，规模最大，全美国1/3的公共交通使用者和2/3的铁路乘客居住于纽约都会区<ref name="MTAinfo">{{Cite web |title=The MTA Network: Public Transportation for the New York Region |url=http://www.mta.info/mta/network.htm |accessdate=2012-08-30 |publisher=Metropolitan Transportation Authority |archive-date=2011-12-30 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111230115423/http://www.mta.info/mta/network.htm |dead-url=yes }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=Commuting in America III: Commuting Facts |url=http://onlinepubs.trb.org/onlinepubs/nchrp/CIAIIIfacts.pdf |accessdate=2012-08-30 |author=Pisarski, Alan |date=2006-10-16 |format=PDF |publisher=Transportation Research Board |archive-date=2008-08-24 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080824013626/http://onlinepubs.trb.org/onlinepubs/nchrp/CIAIIIfacts.pdf |dead-url=no }}</ref>。著名的[[纽约地铁|纽约地铁]]是[[世界城市轨道交通年乘客量列表|西半球最为繁忙的轨道交通系统]]，而[[大中央车站|大中央车站]]则是全球月台数最多的火车站。纽约还拥有世界上最繁忙的[[纽约市机场|空域]]之一。[[乔治华盛顿大桥|乔治华盛顿大桥]]连接曼哈顿和新泽西州[[博根县|博根县]]，是世界上最繁忙的机动车桥梁<ref>{{Cite web |title=Port Authority of New York and New Jersey - George Washington Bridge |url=http://www.panynj.gov/bridges-tunnels/george-washington-bridge.html |accessdate=2013-09-13 |publisher=The Port Authority of New York & New Jersey |archive-date=2013-09-20 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130920192211/http://www.panynj.gov/bridges-tunnels/george-washington-bridge.html |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=GW Bridge Painters: Dangerous Job on Top of the World's Busiest Bridge |url=http://abcnews.go.com/US/george-washington-bridge-painters-dangerous-job-top-worlds/story?id=17771877 |accessdate=2013-09-13 |author=Bod Woodruff, Lana Zak, and Stephanie Wash |date=2012-11-20 |publisher=ABC News |archive-date=2013-09-28 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130928002159/http://abcnews.go.com/US/george-washington-bridge-painters-dangerous-job-top-worlds/story?id=17771877 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

公共交通在纽约广受欢迎。2005年，54.6%的纽约人運用公共交通系統上班<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://money.cnn.com/2007/06/13/real_estate/public_transit_commutes/index.htm |title=New Yorkers are Top Transit Users |author=Les Christie |date=2007-06-29 |work=CNNMoney.com |publisher=Cable News Network |accessdate=2008-01-02 |archive-date=2008-05-16 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080516222801/http://money.cnn.com/2007/06/13/real_estate/public_transit_commutes/index.htm |dead-url=no }}</ref>，而在美国其他地方，90%的人驾车上班，与之形成鲜明对比<ref name="2001summary">{{Cite web |title=NHTS 2001 Highlights Report, BTS03-05 |url=http://www.bts.gov/publications/highlights_of_the_2001_national_household_travel_survey/pdf/entire.pdf |accessdate=2008-09-01 |year=2001 |format=PDF |publisher=U.S. Department of Transportation, Bureau of Transportation Statistics |archive-date=2005-05-14 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20050514220419/http://www.bts.gov/publications/highlights_of_the_2001_national_household_travel_survey/pdf/entire.pdf |dead-url=yes }}</ref>。根据美国人口调查局调查，纽约居民每日花费38.4分钟前往上班，在全国大城市中时间最长<ref>{{Cite web |title=New York Has Longest Commute to Work in Nation, American Community Survey Finds |url=http://www.census.gov/Press-Release/www/releases/archives/american_community_survey_acs/001695.html |accessdate=2008-03-15 |date=December 2004 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080313083657/http://www.census.gov/Press-Release/www/releases/archives/american_community_survey_acs/001695.html |archivedate=2008-03-13 |deadurl=yes}}</ref>，但由于公共交通的使用率较高，他们同时花费（相对于家庭收入）也较少，与其他城市居民相比，每年总共在交通上省下190亿美元<ref>{{Cite web |title=New York City's Green Dividend |url=http://www.streetsblog.org/2010/04/21/sustainable-transport-saves-new-yorkers-19-billion-per-year/ |accessdate=2012-01-26 |publisher=CEOs for Cities |archive-date=2016-11-01 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161101135006/http://www.streetsblog.org/2010/04/21/sustainable-transport-saves-new-yorkers-19-billion-per-year/ |dead-url=yes }}</ref>。

