纽约由[[美铁|美铁]]服务，车站分別位位于[[紐約賓夕法尼亞車站|宾夕法尼亚车站]]及[[大中央總站|大中央車站]]，连接[[东北走廊|东北走廊]]的[[波士顿|波士顿]]、[[费城|费城]]和[[华盛顿哥伦比亚特区|华盛顿特区]]，以及提供通往其他北美城市的长途服务。[[纽新航港局客运总站|纽新航港局客运总站]]是纽约[[城际巴士服务|城际巴士服务]]的总站，也是全球最繁忙的巴士站，每日服务7,000辆巴士和200,000名乘客<ref>{{Cite press release |title=Architect Chosen for Planned Office Tower Above Port Authority Bus Terminal's North Wing |url=http://www.panynj.gov/AboutthePortAuthority/PressCenter/PressReleases/PressRelease/index.php?id=1154 |publisher=[[紐約與新澤西港務局|Port Authority of New York and New Jersey]] |date=2008-11-17 |accessdate=2009-05-17 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090222025919/http://www.panynj.gov/AboutthePortAuthority/PressCenter/PressReleases/PressRelease/index.php?id=1154 |archivedate=2009-02-22}}</ref>。

纽约地铁的車站达到468个，数目为全球最多，线路为美國最长，近年乘客数量約居世界第七位。值得注意的是，纽约地铁保持24小时运行，而多数城市则在夜间停止营运，[[港鐵|香港]]<ref>{{Cite web |title=Service Hours |url=http://www.mtr.com.hk/eng/getting_around/service_hours.html |accessdate=2012-07-31 |publisher=MTR |archive-date=2012-09-29 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120929044142/http://www.mtr.com.hk/eng/getting_around/service_hours.html |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=Tsuen Wan Line |url=http://www.travelchinaguide.com/cityguides/hongkong/transportation/metro-tsuenwan-line.htm |accessdate=2012-07-31 |publisher=TravelChinaGuide.com |archive-date=2012-10-20 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121020051225/http://www.travelchinaguide.com/cityguides/hongkong/transportation/metro-tsuenwan-line.htm |dead-url=no }}</ref>、[[伦敦地铁|伦敦]]、[[巴黎地铁|巴黎]]、[[上海地铁|上海]]、[[韩国首都圈电铁|首尔]]<ref>{{Cite web |title=Train Time Table - Search station |url=http://www.smrt.co.kr/program/Eng/Subway/Train/Station_select.jsp?main=Y |accessdate=2012-08-29 |publisher=[[首尔特别市都市铁道公社|Seoul Metropolitan Rapid Transit Corporation]] |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120216194130/http://www.smrt.co.kr/program/Eng/Subway/Train/Station_select.jsp?main=Y |archivedate=2012-02-16 |deadurl=yes}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=Subway map |url=http://www.smrt.co.kr/program/cyberStation/main2.jsp?lang=e# |accessdate=2012-08-29 |publisher=Seoul Metropolitan Rapid Transit Corporation |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120414225109/http://www.smrt.co.kr/program/cyberStation/main2.jsp?lang=e |archivedate=2012-04-14 |deadurl=yes}}</ref>和[[東京的地下鐵系統|东京]]都不例外。

纽约的交通系统还包括全美洲最长的[[悬索桥|悬索桥]]、同时也是世界最长悬索桥之一的[[韦拉札诺海峡大桥|韦拉札诺海峡大桥]]<ref name="infoplease.com">{{Cite web |title=Longest Suspension Bridges in the World |url=http://www.infoplease.com/toptens/worldsuspbridges.html |accessdate=2012-09-07 |publisher=Pearson Education |archive-date=2012-08-10 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120810050845/http://www.infoplease.com/toptens/worldsuspbridges.html |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="Verrazano-Narrows Bridge">{{Cite web |title=Verrazano-Narrows Bridge |url=http://www.nycroads.com/crossings/verrazano-narrows/ |accessdate=2012-09-07 |publisher=Eastern Roads |archive-date=2018-10-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181006093425/http://www.nycroads.com/crossings/verrazano-narrows/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>，世界第一条机械通风的行车隧道[[荷兰隧道|荷兰隧道]]<ref name="nhlsum">{{Cite web |title=Holland Tunnel |url=http://tps.cr.nps.gov/nhl/detail.cfm?ResourceId=2176&ResourceType=Structure |accessdate=2012-03-22 |work=National Historic Landmark Quicklinks |publisher=[[美国国家公园管理局|National Park Service]] |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140629011542/http://tps.cr.nps.gov/nhl/detail.cfm?ResourceId=2176&ResourceType=Structure |archivedate=2014-06-29 |deadurl=yes}}</ref>，超过12,000辆{{Link-en|纽约出租车|Taxicabs of New York City|黄色出租车}}<ref>{{Cite web |title=The State of the NYC Taxi |url=http://www.nyc.gov/html/tlc/downloads/pdf/state_of_taxi.pdf |accessdate=2008-09-01 |date=2006-03-09 |format=PDF |publisher=New York City Taxi and Limousine Commission |archive-date=2010-12-25 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20101225070939/http://www.nyc.gov/html/tlc/downloads/pdf/state_of_taxi.pdf |dead-url=no }}</ref>，连接[[罗斯福岛_(纽约)|罗斯福岛]]和曼哈顿岛的[[罗斯福岛空中缆车|罗斯福岛空中缆车]]，以及将曼哈顿与城内城外诸多地点连接起来的渡轮系统。

[[File:JFK_Plane_Queue.jpg|缩略图]]是北美[[全球机场国际客量列表|国际旅客吞吐量最多的机场]]<ref>[http://www.aci.aero/cda/aci_common/display/main/aci_content07_c.jsp?zn=aci&cp=1-5-212-1376-1379_666_2__ 2011 Year-to-date International Passenger Traffic (as of December 2011)] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20101206022153/http://www.aci.aero/cda/aci_common/display/main/aci_content07_c.jsp?zn=aci&cp=1-5-212-1376-1379_666_2__ |date=2010-12-06 }}</ref>]]
[[史泰登岛渡轮|史泰登岛渡轮]]是全美最繁忙的渡轮线路，每年搭载近2000万旅客往来于斯塔滕岛和曼哈顿下城间{{convert|5.2|mi|km}}的水域<ref>{{Cite web |title=The Staten Island Ferry |url=http://www.siferry.com/ |accessdate=2013-01-19 |publisher=SIFerry.com. |dead-url=yes |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110923160017/http://www.siferry.com/ |archive-date=2011-09-23}}</ref>。[[斯塔滕岛铁路|斯塔滕岛铁路]]系统专为斯塔滕岛服务。[[纽新港務局过哈德逊河捷运|纽新港務局过哈德逊河捷运]]连接曼哈顿下城与新泽西州东北部，主要目的地为[[霍博肯_(新泽西州)|霍博肯]]、[[泽西市|泽西市]]和[[纽瓦克_(新泽西州)|纽瓦克]]，同样24小时营运，这意味着全球四个24小时营运的快速交通系统中有两个位于纽约（另两个是[[芝加哥地铁|芝加哥地铁]]的部分线路及[[费城|费城]]的[[港务局交通公司高速线|港务局交通公司高速线]]）。

纽约的公共巴士数量为北美最多，通勤铁路系统为北美最大<ref name="MTAinfo" />。这一铁路系统由[[长岛铁路|长岛铁路]]、[[大都会北方铁路|大都会北方铁路]]和[[新泽西公共交通公司|新泽西公共交通公司]]组成，将纽约市与市郊三州地区连接起来，最后汇集于大中央车站和宾夕法尼亚车站，总共包括超过250个车站和20条线路<ref name="MTAinfo" /><ref>{{Cite web |title=About the MTA Long Island Rail Road |url=http://www.mta.nyc.ny.us/lirr/pubs/aboutlirr.htm |accessdate=2008-09-01 |publisher=Metropolitan Transportation Authority |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080913074913/http://www.mta.nyc.ny.us/lirr/pubs/aboutlirr.htm |archivedate=2008-09-13 |deadurl=yes}}</ref>。

纽约是国际空乘旅客进入美国的大门<ref name="IntlTravel">{{Cite web |title=U.S. International Travel and Transportation Trends, BTS02-03 |url=http://www.bts.gov/publications/us_international_travel_and_transportation_trends/2002/index.html |accessdate=2008-09-01 |year=2002 |publisher=U.S. Department of Transportation, Bureau of Transportation Statistics |dead-url=yes |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20081026120015/http://www.bts.gov/publications/us_international_travel_and_transportation_trends/2002/index.html |archive-date=2008-10-26}}</ref>，这一地区有三大主要机场，分别为[[约翰·肯尼迪国际机场|约翰·肯尼迪国际机场]]、[[纽瓦克自由国际机场|纽瓦克自由国际机场]]和[[拉瓜迪亚机场|拉瓜迪亚机场]]。纽约有全美最繁忙的空域，2005年使用三个机场的旅客达到1亿人次<ref>{{Cite web |title=2005 Annual Airport Traffic Report |url=http://www.panynj.gov/CommutingTravel/airports/pdfs/traffic/Air_Traffic_2005.pdf |accessdate=2012-07-30 |date=2006-11-02 |format=PDF |publisher=The Port Authority of New York and New Jersey |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070605013009/http://www.panynj.gov/CommutingTravel/airports/pdfs/traffic/Air_Traffic_2005.pdf |archivedate=2007-06-05 |deadurl=yes}}</ref>，2004年从肯尼迪国际机场和纽瓦克国际机场出国的旅客占全美的四分之一<ref>{{Cite press release |url=http://www.panynj.gov/AboutthePortAuthority/PressCenter/PressReleases/PressRelease/index.php?id=724 |title=Port Authority Leads Nation in Record-Setting Year for Travel Abroad |publisher=The Port Authority of New York and New Jersey |date=2005-08-29 |accessdate=2007-02-18 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20061002172453/http://www.panynj.gov/AboutthePortAuthority/PressCenter/PressReleases/PressRelease/index.php?id=724 |archivedate=2006-10-02}}</ref>。[[纽约与新泽西港務局|纽约与新泽西港務局]]还计划通过第四个机场来扩充旅客规模，即位于纽约州[[紐堡_(紐約州)|纽堡]]附近的{{Link-en|斯图尔特国际机场|Stewart International Airport}}<ref>{{Cite web |title=Stewart International Airport upgrade approved as Port Authority aims to increase passenger traffic |url=http://www.nj.com/news/index.ssf/2012/05/stewart_international_airport.html |accessdate=2012-07-30 |author=Steve Strunsky |date=2012-05-31 |publisher=New Jersey On-Line LLC. |archive-date=2019-01-11 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190111233204/https://www.nj.com/news/index.ssf/2012/05/stewart_international_airport.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

[[File:Verrazano.jpg|缩略图]]是全球最长的[[悬索桥|悬索桥]]之一<ref name="infoplease.com" /><ref name="Verrazano-Narrows Bridge" />，横跨{{Link-en|韦拉札诺海峡|The Narrows}}，连接[[布鲁克林|布鲁克林]]和[[斯塔滕岛|斯塔滕岛]]]]
纽约的高公共交通使用率、近120,000名单车者<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.gothamgazette.com/article/transportation/20060718/16/1910/ |title=Biking It |author=Schaller, Bruce |date=June 2006 |publisher=Gotham Gazette |accessdate=2008-09-01 |archive-date=2007-09-30 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070930203645/http://www.gothamgazette.com/article/transportation/20060718/16/1910/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>和为数众多的步行上班者使之成为美国最为节能的城市<ref name="NYC energy consumption" />。步行和单车占全市交通方式的21%，而在全国范围内为8%<ref>{{Cite web |title=2001 National Household Travel Survey: Summary of Travel Trends |url=http://nhts.ornl.gov/2001/pub/STT.pdf |accessdate=2008-09-01 |date=December 2004 |format=PDF |publisher=U.S. Department of Transportation |archive-date=2018-02-21 |archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/6xOm8bFVA?url=http://nhts.ornl.gov/2001/pub/STT.pdf |dead-url=no }}</ref>。2011年，纽约被评为全美最适宜步行的城市<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.sfgate.com/cgi-bin/article.cgi?f=/c/a/2011/07/20/BUUK1KCC67.DTL&tsp=1 |title=S.F., Oakland in Top 10 Most Walkable U.S. Cities |last=Said |first=Carolyn |date=2011-07-20 |work=San Francisco Chronicle |accessdate=2011-07-20 |archive-date=2012-05-16 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120516141633/http://www.sfgate.com/cgi-bin/article.cgi?f=%2Fc%2Fa%2F2011%2F07%2F20%2FBUUK1KCC67.DTL&tsp=1 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=The 10 Most Walkable U.S. Cities |url=http://www.marketwatch.com/story/the-10-most-walkable-us-cities-2011-07-20?link=MW_popular |accessdate=2011-07-20 |year=2011 |work=MarketWatch |archive-date=2021-04-07 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210407070401/https://www.marketwatch.com/story/the-10-most-walkable-us-cities-2011-07-20?link=MW_popular |dead-url=no }}</ref>。2013年夏季，[[花旗银行|花旗银行]]为纽约市赞助10,000辆公共单车<ref>{{Cite web |title=The Summer Bicycles Took Control |url=http://www.theatlantic.com/health/archive/2013/06/the-summer-bicycles-took-control/277166/ |accessdate=2013-06-28 |author=James Hamblin |date=2013-06-28 |work=The Atlantic Monthly |publisher=The Atlantic Monthly Group |archive-date=2021-04-17 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210417170219/https://www.theatlantic.com/health/archive/2013/06/the-summer-bicycles-took-control/277166/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>，[[昆尼皮亚克大学|昆尼皮亚克大学]]的调查表明大部分纽约人都支持这一单车共享计划<ref>{{Cite web |title=NEW YORK CITY VOTERS BACK MAYOR’S STORM PLAN 4-1, QUINNIPIAC UNIVERSITY POLL FINDS; SLIM MAJORITY BACKS FOOD RECYCLING, BIKE RENTALS |url=http://www.quinnipiac.edu/images/polling/nyc/nyc06272013.pdf/ |accessdate=2013-06-28 |author=Pat Smith |date=2013-06-27 |coauthors=Maurice Carroll |format=PDF |work=Quinnipiac University Poll |publisher=Quinnipiac University |archive-date=2013-07-03 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130703024203/http://www.quinnipiac.edu/images/polling/nyc/nyc06272013.pdf/ |dead-url=yes }}</ref>。

纽约还拥有庞大的[[高速公路|高速公路]]网络，与其公共交通系统相互补充，将之与新泽西州北部、[[西徹斯特郡|威斯特徹斯特县]]、[[长岛_(纽约)|长岛]]及西南[[康涅狄格州|康涅狄格州]]通过数条桥梁与隧道连接起来。由于这些公路同时也是数百万市郊居民入城上班的干道，长达数小时的[[交通堵塞|交通堵塞]]状况几乎每日都会发生，在[[繁忙時間|高峰时段]]尤其如此<ref name="recordonline.com">[http://www.recordonline.com/apps/pbcs.dll/article?AID=/20061024/BIZ/610240312/-1/NEWS03 George Washington Bridge turns 75 years old: Huge flag, cake part of celebration] {{Wayback|url=http://www.recordonline.com/apps/pbcs.dll/article?AID=%2F20061024%2FBIZ%2F610240312%2F-1%2FNEWS03 |date=20180708134712 }}, ''{{tsl|en|Times Herald-Record||Times Herald-Record}}'', October 24, 2006. "The party, however, will be small in comparison to the one that the Port Authority of New York and New Jersey organized for 5,000 people to open the bridge to traffic in 1931. And it won't even be on ''what is now the world's busiest bridge'' for fear of snarling traffic."</ref>。

纽约虽然对公共交通相当依赖，但道路仍然是城市的重要组成部分。{{Link-en|1811年委员会计划|Commissioners' Plan of 1811|曼哈顿的道路布局}}在很大程度上影响了该市的发展。纽约的许多道路都成为了某一项产业的[[转喻|代名词]]，例如[[百老汇|百老汇]]之于戏剧<ref>{{Cite web |title=THE MYTHS AND METAPHORS OF MUSIC AND DANCE SINGIN' IN THE RAIN |url=http://hofprints.hofstra.edu/2/02/The_Myths_and_Metaphors_of_Music_and_Dance_Singin'_in_the_Rain.html |accessdate=2012-02-06 |publisher=Hofstra University |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20060902162226/http://hofprints.hofstra.edu/2/02/The_Myths_and_Metaphors_of_Music_and_Dance_Singin%27_in_the_Rain.html |archivedate=2006-09-02 |deadurl=yes}}</ref>，[[华尔街|华尔街]]之于金融<ref>{{Cite web |title=Grammar & Composition metonymy |url=http://grammar.about.com/od/mo/g/metonymy.htm |accessdate=2012-02-06 |author=Richard Nordquist |publisher=About.com |archive-date=2017-02-28 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170228130252/http://grammar.about.com/od/mo/g/metonymy.htm |dead-url=no }}</ref>，[[麦迪逊大道|麦迪逊大道]]之于广告<ref>{{Cite web |title=Definition of Metonymy |url=http://www.chegg.com/homework-help/definitions/metonymy-39 |accessdate=2013-05-09 |publisher=Chegg, Inc |archiveurl=http://arquivo.pt/wayback/20160522170012/http%3A//www.chegg.com/homework%2Dhelp/definitions/metonymy%2D39 |archivedate=2016-05-22 |deadurl=yes}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=Metonymy vs Synecdoche |url=http://www.buzzle.com/articles/metonymy-vs-synecdoche.html |accessdate=2012-02-06 |publisher=2012 Buzzle.com |dead-url=yes |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111102154357/http://www.buzzle.com/articles/metonymy-vs-synecdoche.html |archive-date=2011-11-02}}</ref>和[[第七大道|第七大道]]之于时尚。

